by the Roses. It's Megars.

239
00:20:11,028 --> 00:20:13,496
Dr. Alex Cross.
Special agent in charge...

240
00:20:13,564 --> 00:20:15,532
- Oliver MacArthur.
- How do you do. Sir.

241
00:20:15,599 --> 00:20:17,999
Alex. I'll catch you later.

242
00:20:18,068 --> 00:20:20,434
- Forensics.
- Yes. Sir.

243
00:20:20,504 --> 00:20:23,132
Senator and Mrs. Rose
are through here.

244
00:20:23,207 --> 00:20:28,372
Before we talk to them. You any
idea why Soneji is involving you?

245
00:20:28,445 --> 00:20:31,778
- Not at all.
- This way.

246
00:20:31,849 --> 00:20:35,683
Uh. Excuse me. Shouldn't Agent
Flannigan be in the room with us?

247
00:20:35,753 --> 00:20:38,517
Not a good idea.
Miss Flannigan is not welcome.

248
00:20:38,589 --> 00:20:41,217
But she's
a material witness.

249
00:20:41,292 --> 00:20:45,160
She failed the Roses.
And she failed the Service.

250
00:20:45,229 --> 00:20:47,356
I think Agent MacArthur
has a point.

251
00:20:47,431 --> 00:20:50,059
No. He's missing
the point.

252
00:20:50,134 --> 00:20:53,228
You saw Soneji every day.
Five days a week. For how long?

253
00:20:53,304 --> 00:20:55,636
Two years.

254
00:20:55,706 --> 00:20:59,198
You have no idea how much
you know about this case.

255
00:21:05,215 --> 00:21:07,274
Agent Flannigan.

256
00:21:11,088 --> 00:21:15,388
They say that when I die.
The case will die.

257
00:21:15,459 --> 00:21:19,190
They say it'll be
like a book I close.

258
00:21:19,263 --> 00:21:23,597
But the book,
it will never close.

259
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:26,033
[Alex On Tape]
Very poetic. What the hell is it?

260
00:21:26,103 --> 00:21:29,903
[Soneji] I've left you
something for your visit...

261
00:21:29,974 --> 00:21:31,965
with the Roses tonight.

262
00:21:32,042 --> 00:21:37,002
You'll find it in your cold,
corrugated mailbox.

263
00:21:37,081 --> 00:21:39,072
[Recorder Clicks Off]

264
00:21:42,453 --> 00:21:45,945
Well. For what it's won'th.
That's Soneji.

265
00:21:46,023 --> 00:21:48,890
His speech patterrs
the same.

266
00:21:48,959 --> 00:21:52,895
Is he. Um...

267
00:21:52,963 --> 00:21:56,126
Are we dealing with
a sex maniac?

268
00:21:56,200 --> 00:21:59,727
Someone who might,
you know...

269
00:22:00,738 --> 00:22:02,968
No. Sir.

270
00:22:03,040 --> 00:22:05,531
This man has no such interest
in your daughter.

271
00:22:05,609 --> 00:22:07,804
She's merely a means
to an end.

272
00:22:07,878 --> 00:22:10,073
What do you mean?

273
00:22:10,147 --> 00:22:14,880
I see no standard procedure
in anything he's done.

274
00:22:14,952 --> 00:22:16,943
I disagree.
This is a professional kidnapping.

275
00:22:17,021 --> 00:22:20,047
It's going to be about money.
Which is good.

276
00:22:21,392 --> 00:22:23,792
But you're saying
it isn't about money.

277
00:22:26,463 --> 00:22:28,556
I think he wants to
draw this out.

278
00:22:30,134 --> 00:22:33,069
From what he said,
whatever his motives...

279
00:22:35,773 --> 00:22:38,742
it's very unusual.

280
00:22:41,745 --> 00:22:43,679
What did he mean
about the book?

281
00:22:43,747 --> 00:22:46,238
That it will never close?

282
00:22:49,486 --> 00:22:51,681
I honestly don't know.

283
00:22:51,755 --> 00:22:54,417
Well. I think I do.

284
00:22:56,527 --> 00:23:00,588
Let me tell you
what this Gary Soneji is up to.

285
00:23:00,664 --> 00:23:04,293
The last thing he wants
is good crisis management.

286
00:23:04,368 --> 00:23:07,201
What he wants is to confuse.
Rancor.

287
00:23:07,271 --> 00:23:10,672
Mixed signals, disorientation,
those are his tools.

288
00:23:10,741 --> 00:23:13,266
So. He calls a local cop.

289
00:23:13,343 --> 00:23:17,143
A damaged cop, shouldering
some heavy baggage.

290
00:23:17,214 --> 00:23:19,648
He's using Dr. Cross
as his messenger...

291
00:23:19,716 --> 00:23:22,810
Excuse me. The man that kidnapped
our daughter didn't call you.

292
00:23:22,886 --> 00:23:24,820
So your agenda is what?

293
00:23:24,888 --> 00:23:29,348
- To insult the man he did call?
- Mrs. Rose. I never intended...

294
00:23:29,426 --> 00:23:32,691
No, you wait a second.
A madman has our daughter,

295
00:23:32,763 --> 00:23:35,960
and for some reason
he contacted this man.

296
00:23:36,033 --> 00:23:39,002
Do you know why?

297
00:23:40,771 --> 00:23:44,172
No. Ma'am. Not yet.

298
00:24:21,178 --> 00:24:23,612
Hello.

299
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:25,841
You okay?

300
00:24:27,484 --> 00:24:30,476
You. Uh...

301
00:24:32,189 --> 00:24:35,249
got any tips
for helpless situations?

302
00:24:37,227 --> 00:24:39,388
Well. You could
smoke a can'ton a day.

303
00:24:41,265 --> 00:24:43,893
Or you could bounce back.

304
00:24:43,967 --> 00:24:47,630
Yeah. Well. I don't see
anywhere to bounce to.

305
00:24:47,704 --> 00:24:50,070
Like to get out of here?

306
00:24:58,048 --> 00:25:01,484
Can I ask you something?

307
00:25:01,552 --> 00:25:03,543
Sure.

308
00:25:06,456 --> 00:25:10,483
What did MacArthur mean
when he referred to you as damaged?

309
00:25:13,797 --> 00:25:17,289
Last summer. I let a sting operation
get out of control.

310
00:25:19,136 --> 00:25:21,468
My partner was killed.

311
00:25:25,542 --> 00:25:27,442
[Whistling]

312
00:25:36,587 --> 00:25:40,455
Hello. Megan.
How are you?

313
00:25:40,524 --> 00:25:43,687
Coming to see you.

314
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:45,751
Do you recognize my voice?

315
00:25:48,865 --> 00:25:51,857
It's me.

316
00:25:51,935 --> 00:25:54,665
Mr. Soneji. Hmm?

317
00:25:56,907 --> 00:25:59,705
I brought you that.
A lovely cup of tea with honey.

318
00:25:59,776 --> 00:26:02,677
I know your throat is sore.
It'll make you feel better.

319
00:26:02,746 --> 00:26:06,546
There you go.
It's all right.

320
00:26:09,386 --> 00:26:11,320
You have nothing
to be scared of. Megan.

321
00:26:11,388 --> 00:26:14,380
I'm not scared.

322
00:26:14,458 --> 00:26:20,192
Good. But you're wondering
what's going on.

323
00:26:20,264 --> 00:26:24,496
I know what's going on. You're a
kidnapper. And you're a sick weirdo.

324
00:26:24,568 --> 00:26:27,935
[Laughing]

325
00:26:28,005 --> 00:26:31,566
Megan. You're the most
opinionated girl in my class.

326
00:26:31,642 --> 00:26:35,078
- Think you got that from your mom?
- I wanna go home.

327
00:26:35,145 --> 00:26:39,479
You will. Just promise me
you're going to behave yourself.

328
00:26:39,549 --> 00:26:44,350
Okay?
So. Now listen.

329
00:26:44,421 --> 00:26:48,221
If you need to use the bathroom
or anything. Just press that. Okay?

330
00:26:48,292 --> 00:26:51,227
I wanna go home! Now!

331
00:26:51,295 --> 00:26:53,889
- I brought you some fresh clothes.
- Please!

332
00:26:53,964 --> 00:26:57,073
Mr. Soneji. Please!

333
00:26:57,207 --> 00:26:59,107
[Gun Clicks]

334
00:26:59,175 --> 00:27:01,666
This is a fine gun.

335
00:27:01,745 --> 00:27:06,512
It's Turkish.
Handmade. 1924.

336
00:27:06,583 --> 00:27:08,744
That is nice.

337
00:27:08,818 --> 00:27:11,810
My daddy won it in a game
of poker. Aces and eights.

338
00:27:11,888 --> 00:27:15,255
Dead mars hand.

339
00:27:15,325 --> 00:27:18,453
That's about as much
as I know about my father.

340
00:27:18,528 --> 00:27:21,019
Have a seat.

341
00:27:26,836 --> 00:27:30,932
Do you know of any relationship
between Amy Masterson and Soneji?

342
00:27:31,007 --> 00:27:35,171
Amy? No way.
Why do you ask?

343
00:27:35,245 --> 00:27:38,612
He strangled her.

344
00:27:38,681 --> 00:27:41,548
It's an act of passion.

345
00:27:41,618 --> 00:27:44,553
It's a demonstration
of will.

346
00:27:44,621 --> 00:27:47,112
A message.

347
00:27:48,491 --> 00:27:51,289
Take me seriously.
What do you see?

348
00:27:51,361 --> 00:27:54,296
- Dr. Cross...
- Alex.

349
00:27:54,364 --> 00:27:57,663
Alex. Womars intuition.
Third eye. Sixth sense...

350
00:27:57,734 --> 00:27:59,668
whatever it is.
I don't have it.

351
00:27:59,736 --> 00:28:01,795
Sure you do. You just
don't look at it right.

352
00:28:01,871 --> 00:28:03,862
Every face has two aspects.

353
00:28:03,940 --> 00:28:07,569
Now try looking at it down
the middle. One side at a time.

354
00:28:07,644 --> 00:28:10,010
Would you say this man
was confident?

355
00:28:10,079 --> 00:28:12,912
- Yeah.
- Narcissistic?

356
00:28:12,982 --> 00:28:17,316
- L-I wouldn't know.
- Ever see any flashes of hatred?

357
00:28:17,387 --> 00:28:20,754
- No. No. No!
- Anger? Hostility?

358
00:28:20,824 --> 00:28:25,261
Look. Everything about him
was right.

359
00:28:25,328 --> 00:28:29,492
He was always patient. He was
pleasant. He had a sense of humor.

360
00:28:29,566 --> 00:28:32,899
I mean. He was
the perfect teacher.

361
00:28:37,807 --> 00:28:39,775
What do you see?

362
00:28:42,145 --> 00:28:44,113
I see...

363
00:28:44,180 --> 00:28:46,580
No. I mean about me.

364
00:28:48,218 --> 00:28:50,846
What do you see about me?

365
00:28:50,920 --> 00:28:53,889
That's why you're here.
Isn't it?

366
00:28:53,957 --> 00:28:59,862
Size me up. Evaluate
your primary material witness?

367
00:29:03,333 --> 00:29:05,961
I see that you're about
to start an argument.

368
00:29:06,035 --> 00:29:07,900
I need to help get her back.

369
00:29:07,971 --> 00:29:09,734
What makes you think
I want a partner?

370
00:29:09,806 --> 00:29:12,104
- You don't. I can understand that.
- That's right.

371
00:29:12,175 --> 00:29:15,303
- No. You can't.
- Can I tell you why I don't care?

372
00:29:18,248 --> 00:29:20,182
Shoot.

373
00:29:23,519 --> 00:29:28,684
Look. When I was
assigned to Cathedral.

374
00:29:28,758 --> 00:29:30,749
It was a job
I didn't want.

375
00:29:30,827 --> 00:29:34,456
It's a far cry from working
rope lines or flying Air Force One.

376
00:29:34,530 --> 00:29:38,057
But I have been there
for three years.

377
00:29:38,134 --> 00:29:41,934
I have been responsible
for Megan for three years.

378
00:29:42,005 --> 00:29:45,168
And that little girl means
more to me than even a partner.

379
00:29:45,241 --> 00:29:47,903
Can you understand that?

380
00:29:50,280 --> 00:29:52,680
I suppose so.

381
00:29:54,450 --> 00:29:59,080
Even if I say no. You'll probably
follow me around wherever I go.

382
00:30:01,424 --> 00:30:05,258
So. If it's a choice between
having you as a partner...

383
00:30:05,328 --> 00:30:10,994
or as a stalker. I guess I'll
take my chances with a partner.

384
00:30:13,169 --> 00:30:15,103
Thank you.

385
00:30:26,516 --> 00:30:29,849
The student drop-off is there.
That's my morning post.

386
00:30:29,919 --> 00:30:34,913
Students sign in. Cameras are
there. There. There and there.

387
00:30:34,991 --> 00:30:37,482
Motions sensors
all around the periphery.

388
00:30:39,128 --> 00:30:42,325
Foolproof way to keep
the kooks out.

389
00:30:42,398 --> 00:30:46,596
Exactly. We were always looking
in the wrong direction.

390
00:30:46,669 --> 00:30:49,467
- Which door did he go out?
- Uh. That one there.

391
00:30:49,539 --> 00:30:52,201
It's a straight shot
to his parking space.

392
00:30:55,945 --> 00:30:57,936
Let's go in.

393
00:31:05,154 --> 00:31:08,248
- His classroom.
- Mm-hmm.

394
00:31:08,324 --> 00:31:12,658
He was teaching how everything
on the Internet is connected.

395
00:31:14,063 --> 00:31:17,897
Alex. You got a sec?
Sure.

396
00:31:17,967 --> 00:31:21,994
Listen. I think turf wars
are a total waste of time.

397
00:31:22,071 --> 00:31:25,666
If I was out of line
last night. I apologize.

398
00:31:25,742 --> 00:31:28,734
Don't. I've been there.

399
00:31:30,980 --> 00:31:34,177
- Anything you need. Let me know.
- Sure. Mac.

400
00:31:36,052 --> 00:31:38,714
[Agent Hickley] Dr. Cross,
you might want to see this.

401
00:31:46,329 --> 00:31:49,298
- This was Megars desk?
- Yeah.

402
00:31:49,365 --> 00:31:52,334
- What are you doing?
- Scoping GIFs.

403
00:31:52,402 --> 00:31:56,862
Graphic Interchange Formats.
They're all Stego-encrypted.

404
00:31:56,939 --> 00:32:00,067
Somewhere among the billions of
zeros and ones making this image...

405
00:32:00,143 --> 00:32:03,306
- is a string of text.
- I know about this.

406
00:32:03,379 --> 00:32:05,813
It's the cutting-edge method
of passing notes in class.

407
00:32:05,882 --> 00:32:07,941
It's driving the teachers nuts.

408
00:32:08,017 --> 00:32:11,009
How long before
you can access it?

409
00:32:11,087 --> 00:32:13,146
Try never.

410
00:32:13,222 --> 00:32:15,281
You don't crack Stego
without a password.

411
00:32:15,358 --> 00:32:17,326
Would you take me
to his office?

412
00:32:21,697 --> 00:32:24,632
Oh. When you find Soneji.
Ask him for the password.

413
00:32:24,700 --> 00:32:28,136
He planted a monitoring virus
on the girl's hard drive.

414
00:32:28,204 --> 00:32:32,140
Every keystroke Megan hit.
Soneji was recording it.

415
00:32:32,208 --> 00:32:34,301
[Computer Beeping]

416
00:32:38,481 --> 00:32:41,075
Good move. Jezz.

417
00:32:41,150 --> 00:32:44,278
Angling for a position
with the D.C.P.D. I like that.

418
00:32:45,721 --> 00:32:48,554
Dr. Cross.
Agent Ben Devine.

419
00:32:48,624 --> 00:32:51,491
Agent Devine is security
systems supervisor.

420
00:32:51,561 --> 00:32:53,995
Well. For now.

421
00:32:54,063 --> 00:32:56,054
We're going to be thrown
to the wolves.

422
00:32:56,132 --> 00:32:58,657
As soon as they find
Megan Rose dead in a ditch.

423
00:32:58,734 --> 00:33:01,168
Now what makes you so sure
that's what's going to happen?

424
00:33:01,237 --> 00:33:04,434
Me getting fired
or the girl in a ditch?

425
00:33:04,507 --> 00:33:06,771
Sorry.

426
00:33:06,843 --> 00:33:10,609
I'm having
a pessimistic day.

427
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:13,342
Tell me.

428
00:33:13,416 --> 00:33:18,217
Soneji. Did he... did he ever show
any interest in what you do?

429
00:33:18,287 --> 00:33:21,745
How you do it?

430
00:33:21,824 --> 00:33:25,453
The man never talked to me.
I never talked to him.

431
00:33:27,163 --> 00:33:30,155
Well. Thanks
for your time.

432
00:34:08,794 --> 00:34:11,820
- Hello.
- [Thunderclap]

433
00:34:11,897 --> 00:34:13,888
What?

434
00:34:15,367 --> 00:34:17,426
What do you think
that is?

435
00:34:20,739 --> 00:34:25,267
- An empty frame.
- Mm-hmm.

436
00:34:25,344 --> 00:34:27,676
Otherwise known as...

437
00:34:29,748 --> 00:34:32,979
[Jezzie]
A missing picture.

438
00:34:51,704 --> 00:34:54,036
[Chattering]

439
00:35:18,130 --> 00:35:21,896
[Hickley]
You onto something?

440
00:35:43,055 --> 00:35:46,183
Our missing picture.

441
00:35:46,258 --> 00:35:48,192
Mm-hmm.

442
00:35:48,260 --> 00:35:53,095
Our Mr. Soneji
has a sense of humor.

443
00:35:53,165 --> 00:35:56,362
He didn't just kidnap a little girl.
He turned it into a game.

444
00:35:57,436 --> 00:35:59,427
[Whispering]
Okay.

445
00:36:03,108 --> 00:36:05,508
Let's see what you know.
Mr. Lindbergh.

446
00:36:17,523 --> 00:36:19,548
- My. My.
- What do you got?

447
00:36:19,625 --> 00:36:21,616
Dr. Cross isn't
in cyberspace anymore.

448
00:36:21,693 --> 00:36:24,218
You're at a live site.
Iooking through a video camera.

449
00:36:24,296 --> 00:36:26,287
Those arrows down there
move it.

450
00:36:30,536 --> 00:36:33,801
Where are we?

451
00:36:33,872 --> 00:36:36,932
I would guess
we're in Soneji's home.

452
00:36:37,009 --> 00:36:41,639
Now we're supposed to
find out where that is.

453
00:36:41,713 --> 00:36:43,647
[Woman]
Oliver MacArthur's office.

454
00:36:43,715 --> 00:36:45,649
Yeah. It's me. Hold on.

455
00:36:45,717 --> 00:36:48,709
How about the files?

456
00:36:59,765 --> 00:37:02,097
- There... on the wall.
- There's a...

457
00:37:02,167 --> 00:37:04,101
Can you zoom in there?

458
00:37:06,638 --> 00:37:09,732
- [MacArthur] "Jonathan... M"...
- [Jezzie] "E"...

459
00:37:09,808 --> 00:37:12,902
- [Jezzie] "M-E"...
- [Hickley] "L"?

460
00:37:12,978 --> 00:37:15,811
You can't move that around.
Can you? It's stationary.

461
00:37:15,881 --> 00:37:18,372
[Alex] No, there's something
somewhere else, I guarantee that.

462
00:37:18,450 --> 00:37:20,384
- [Hickley] Right there.
- [All] There.

463
00:37:20,452 --> 00:37:22,420
- [Hickley] You can...
- [Agent] Focus.

464
00:37:22,488 --> 00:37:24,786
- Bingo.
- [Hickley] M-E-R...

465
00:37:24,857 --> 00:37:26,791
[Agent]
"Merc"...

466
00:37:26,859 --> 00:37:31,922
"Mercusio.
M-E-R-C-U-S-l-O."

467
00:37:31,997 --> 00:37:35,125
- "Fourteen... thirty-two..."
- [All] "Thirty-five..."

468
00:37:35,200 --> 00:37:37,464
- Granville.
- Gary Soneji is also known as...

469
00:37:37,536 --> 00:37:40,767
Mercusio. Jonathan.
1435 Granville Street.

470
00:37:40,839 --> 00:37:43,273
Well done. Alex.

471
00:37:43,342 --> 00:37:45,537
[Sighs]

472
00:37:50,516 --> 00:37:54,145
[Agent] In. In. In!
[Continues. Indistinct]

473
00:37:54,219 --> 00:37:56,153
Eyes open!

474
00:37:57,589 --> 00:38:00,581
- There.
- [Agents Talking, Indistinct]

475
00:38:07,232 --> 00:38:09,166
[Footsteps Running Upstairs]

476
00:38:09,234 --> 00:38:11,566
[Agent]
Not until we get the go-ahead.

477
00:39:13,632 --> 00:39:16,260
His surveillance
was better than ours.

478
00:39:16,335 --> 00:39:19,327
He's been at this
for years.

479
00:39:24,743 --> 00:39:26,734
Imagine the patience,

480
00:39:26,812 --> 00:39:29,940
the dedication.

481
00:39:32,217 --> 00:39:34,811
You sound like
