01:03:49,084 --> 01:03:51,985
- There's a package for Mr. Antwerp.
- [Dial Tone]

730
01:03:52,054 --> 01:03:54,454
Okay, people, let's move.

731
01:03:57,993 --> 01:04:00,791
- Don't lose him. Kiddo.
- You won't even see me.

732
01:04:10,873 --> 01:04:13,899
[Tires Squealing]

733
01:04:41,370 --> 01:04:44,897
- I'm on police business.
- Eddie. This way.

734
01:04:54,450 --> 01:04:56,384
Hi. How are you?

735
01:04:56,452 --> 01:04:58,511
Do you have a package
for Mr. Antwerp?

736
01:04:58,587 --> 01:05:00,646
Yes.

737
01:05:04,026 --> 01:05:06,324
Yes. Sir.

738
01:05:06,395 --> 01:05:10,092
[Phone Ringing]

739
01:05:10,165 --> 01:05:12,099
Over there. That one.

740
01:05:14,136 --> 01:05:18,300
[Phone Continues Ringing]

741
01:05:21,210 --> 01:05:23,144
[Ring]

742
01:05:23,212 --> 01:05:26,340
- Cross.
- Leave the phone. Leave the car.

743
01:05:26,415 --> 01:05:30,249
Pennsylvania and Sixth.
The fountain. 14 minutes. Run.

744
01:05:30,319 --> 01:05:32,787
Thanks.

745
01:05:32,855 --> 01:05:35,323
- [Cross] Mac. You there?
- Alex.

746
01:05:35,391 --> 01:05:38,087
He made me ditch the car.
Looks like it's a running game.

747
01:05:38,160 --> 01:05:41,186
I'm on my way
to Sixth and Pennsylvania.

748
01:05:43,432 --> 01:05:45,662
I'm left
and behind you, Alex.

749
01:06:07,089 --> 01:06:09,717
Bearing onto Pennsylvania.

750
01:06:09,792 --> 01:06:12,989
[Tires Squealing]

751
01:06:13,062 --> 01:06:16,725
[Ring]

752
01:06:18,734 --> 01:06:20,668
- [Ring]
- Cross.

753
01:06:20,736 --> 01:06:24,228
Twelfth and Madison. Twelve minutes
will get you there. Go.

754
01:06:27,276 --> 01:06:29,801
Unit three.
Ioop on 23rd Street.

755
01:06:29,878 --> 01:06:32,312
Unit six. Take "K" Street
and double back.

756
01:06:39,988 --> 01:06:42,354
You've got four units
on top. Alex.

757
01:06:43,425 --> 01:06:45,518
[Phone Ringing]

758
01:06:46,662 --> 01:06:49,028
[Ring]

759
01:06:50,232 --> 01:06:52,496
- [Ring]
- Cross.

760
01:06:52,568 --> 01:06:55,969
Four minutes. Union Station.
Main entrance.

761
01:06:57,573 --> 01:07:00,736
Jezzie. Union Station.
Main entrance.

762
01:07:00,809 --> 01:07:02,743
[Horn Honking]

763
01:07:04,046 --> 01:07:06,742
It's rush hour.
He's drawing them into a crowd.

764
01:07:22,831 --> 01:07:26,130
[Phone Ringing]

765
01:07:28,871 --> 01:07:33,035
[Ringing]

766
01:07:33,108 --> 01:07:35,770
Hey! Hey!

767
01:07:35,844 --> 01:07:39,007
Don't answer that!
I think it's for me.

768
01:07:39,081 --> 01:07:41,845
- Cross.
- [Hangs Up. Dial Tone]

769
01:07:41,917 --> 01:07:45,318
[Man On P.A.,
Indistinct]

770
01:07:45,387 --> 01:07:48,083
[Phone Ringing]

771
01:07:48,157 --> 01:07:50,557
[Ring]

772
01:07:50,626 --> 01:07:54,027
[Ring]

773
01:07:54,096 --> 01:07:56,030
[Ring]

774
01:07:57,099 --> 01:07:59,033
[Ring]

775
01:07:59,101 --> 01:08:03,003
- Cross.
- Keep this phone. Take the metro.

776
01:08:03,071 --> 01:08:06,131
Platform "A."
You got two minutes. Go!

777
01:08:12,681 --> 01:08:16,913
Jezzie. Metro.
Downstairs. Platform "A."

778
01:08:30,669 --> 01:08:33,035
[Phone Ringing]

779
01:08:33,104 --> 01:08:36,301
- Cross.
- Go to the center of the platform.

780
01:09:12,177 --> 01:09:14,873
[Distorted Voice]
Track 15. go!

781
01:09:37,936 --> 01:09:39,995
[Distorted Voice]
Go to the first car.

782
01:10:02,961 --> 01:10:04,986
[Distorted Voice]
You there yet?

783
01:10:05,063 --> 01:10:07,588
- Yeah, I'm there.
- Go to the left side.

784
01:10:07,666 --> 01:10:11,158
- Open the window.
- These windows don't open.

785
01:10:11,236 --> 01:10:13,761
You're smart, Detective,
improvise.

786
01:10:13,838 --> 01:10:15,772
Quickly.

787
01:10:17,208 --> 01:10:19,267
- Police officer. Everybody. Down!
- [Woman] What?

788
01:10:19,344 --> 01:10:23,303
- Get down! Everybody. Down!
- Come on, outta my way!

789
01:10:24,916 --> 01:10:27,009
[Screams. Gasps]

790
01:10:27,085 --> 01:10:31,522
You ready?
All right. Now. Throw!

791
01:10:47,439 --> 01:10:50,806
[Chattering]

792
01:10:50,942 --> 01:10:53,809
We can neither confirm
nor deny that Gary Soneji...

793
01:10:53,878 --> 01:10:56,813
was involved in the incident
on the MTA train this morning.

794
01:10:56,881 --> 01:10:58,872
We've heard that a ransom
was paid. Comment?

795
01:10:58,950 --> 01:11:02,386
- I can't comment on any of that.
- What about Megan Rose?

796
01:11:02,454 --> 01:11:05,048
I'm not going to go into
any details at this time.

797
01:11:05,123 --> 01:11:07,148
What about Soneji's
state of mind?

798
01:11:07,225 --> 01:11:10,160
I'm not going to comment
on his mental stability.

799
01:11:10,228 --> 01:11:12,492
You can draw
your own conclusions.

800
01:11:12,564 --> 01:11:17,297
Now, Senator Rose has agreed
to make a statement,

801
01:11:17,369 --> 01:11:19,564
- So?
- The file on Soneji.

802
01:11:19,638 --> 01:11:22,607
- Is it still on your kitchen table?
- Yeah. Why?

803
01:11:22,674 --> 01:11:24,608
I'm gonna have
another look at it.

804
01:11:24,676 --> 01:11:28,510
This business about the diamonds.
Money. I didn't see it coming.

805
01:11:28,580 --> 01:11:31,447
[Typing]

806
01:11:31,516 --> 01:11:34,508
I am grateful that
the F.B.I. Is here.

807
01:11:34,586 --> 01:11:39,523
With the objective expertise
to find out where my daughter is.

808
01:11:39,591 --> 01:11:41,525
Secondly, I now...

809
01:11:47,832 --> 01:11:49,959
[Jezzie]
This is worse than killing time.

810
01:11:50,035 --> 01:11:54,938
Yeah. But you'd be amazed at how
often the small. Neglected things...

811
01:11:55,006 --> 01:11:58,305
become the most important.

812
01:11:58,376 --> 01:12:01,937
I just got the feeling
we're missing something.

813
01:12:02,013 --> 01:12:05,471
Maybe I'm in
the wrong line of work.

814
01:12:05,550 --> 01:12:08,986
Maybe I should take on
something less challenging.

815
01:12:09,054 --> 01:12:11,249
You do what you are.
Jezzie.

816
01:12:11,322 --> 01:12:14,189
You mean.
You are what you do.

817
01:12:14,259 --> 01:12:18,161
No. I mean.
You do what you are.

818
01:12:18,229 --> 01:12:21,562
You're born with a gift.

819
01:12:21,633 --> 01:12:26,161
If not that. Then you get good
at something along the way.

820
01:12:26,237 --> 01:12:29,570
And what you're good at.
You don't take for granted.

821
01:12:29,641 --> 01:12:31,768
You don't betray it.

822
01:12:34,512 --> 01:12:37,777
What if you do
betray your gift?

823
01:12:37,849 --> 01:12:42,752
Then. You betray yourself.
That's a sad thing.

824
01:12:42,821 --> 01:12:45,221
[Siren Wailing In Distance]

825
01:12:45,290 --> 01:12:47,315
[Knock At Door]

826
01:12:48,960 --> 01:12:51,793
- Who is it?
- [Man] Police.

827
01:12:53,331 --> 01:12:55,822
[Electrical Charge]

828
01:13:00,672 --> 01:13:02,606
Gary Soneji.

829
01:13:02,674 --> 01:13:05,302
Hi. Alex.

830
01:13:07,679 --> 01:13:12,514
Now. Right hand. Thumb and
forefinger. Just give me the gun.

831
01:13:15,386 --> 01:13:19,789
Alex. You can't shoot me.
You'll never find Megan.

832
01:13:35,240 --> 01:13:37,504
Sit down. Alex.

833
01:13:45,617 --> 01:13:48,552
I'm-I'm a little concerned. Alex.
I'm a little...

834
01:13:48,620 --> 01:13:51,214
I'm a little worried
that you...

835
01:13:51,289 --> 01:13:53,780
you don't really care
to understand me anymore;

836
01:13:53,858 --> 01:13:56,019
that you won't paint
an accurate portrait.

837
01:13:56,094 --> 01:13:58,927
And I need you to convince me
that I'm wrong.

838
01:13:58,997 --> 01:14:02,091
In order to do that. We're going
to have to talk about Megan Rose.

839
01:14:02,167 --> 01:14:07,264
No. No bargaining. Alex.
No cheap interrogation techniques.

840
01:14:07,338 --> 01:14:09,829
It's transparent.
And it's clumsy.

841
01:14:09,908 --> 01:14:12,934
This is between
me and you.

842
01:14:13,011 --> 01:14:15,639
I want you to see.

843
01:14:15,713 --> 01:14:21,618
I want you to look inside here
and tell me what the fuck you see!

844
01:14:22,954 --> 01:14:24,945
I'm a gift to you, Alex.

845
01:14:25,023 --> 01:14:28,789
I'm a gift to you.

846
01:14:28,860 --> 01:14:34,127
And you are beyond... pitiful
if you cannot understand that.

847
01:14:35,533 --> 01:14:38,195
I'm living proof
that a mind...

848
01:14:39,871 --> 01:14:42,237
the mind is
a terrible thing.

849
01:14:43,842 --> 01:14:48,870
[Laughing]

850
01:14:52,917 --> 01:14:55,249
I see you've got
your sense of humor back.

851
01:14:55,320 --> 01:14:58,084
[Laughing]
Yeah.

852
01:14:58,156 --> 01:15:01,421
I wondered what happened to it
during the ransom drop.

853
01:15:04,829 --> 01:15:06,763
The ransom drop.

854
01:15:06,831 --> 01:15:09,561
That was
a well-earned 12 million.

855
01:15:10,768 --> 01:15:13,396
Twelve million.

856
01:15:15,440 --> 01:15:18,102
Senator Rose says
he can pull strings.

857
01:15:18,176 --> 01:15:22,112
He says he can fix it so you
keep the 12 million and walk.

858
01:15:22,180 --> 01:15:26,991
All you have to do is return
the child. Where is Megan?

859
01:15:28,125 --> 01:15:32,152
Where's Megan?
Where is Megan?

860
01:15:32,229 --> 01:15:37,428
Where's Megan? Where is Megan?
Where is Megan?

861
01:15:37,501 --> 01:15:40,493
She's trapped on my boat. Alex.
Isn't that right?

862
01:15:40,571 --> 01:15:45,201
Or maybe she's stuck in a warehouse
somewhere or floating in a river.

863
01:15:45,276 --> 01:15:48,211
Swinging from the end
of a rope. Buried alive.

864
01:15:49,513 --> 01:15:51,606
[Snickers]

865
01:15:53,417 --> 01:15:55,385
I envy her.

866
01:15:58,889 --> 01:16:02,120
What would life had been like
with parents like that?

867
01:16:02,193 --> 01:16:05,754
Come on, Gary, blaming your parents
for what you are?

868
01:16:05,830 --> 01:16:08,458
I'm not blaming them, Alex.

869
01:16:08,532 --> 01:16:12,229
They've been punished
already.

870
01:16:17,608 --> 01:16:20,941
I burned down the house
while they slept.

871
01:16:25,516 --> 01:16:28,485
I was 15 years old.

872
01:16:28,552 --> 01:16:31,282
Was it what you expected?

873
01:16:32,890 --> 01:16:36,018
Not really.
It was a new experience.

874
01:16:36,093 --> 01:16:38,027
What. Killing?

875
01:16:38,095 --> 01:16:41,963
No. Being
in the newspapers.

876
01:16:45,236 --> 01:16:48,967
So, in your opinion, Doctor,

877
01:16:49,039 --> 01:16:53,703
were my actions
triggered by nature...

878
01:16:53,778 --> 01:16:55,837
or nurture?

879
01:16:56,947 --> 01:16:59,415
If you want me
to be brutally honest...

880
01:17:00,918 --> 01:17:05,514
I think you just have
a morbid desire to burn in hell.

881
01:17:10,294 --> 01:17:12,489
[Quietly]
We're done for today.

882
01:17:15,266 --> 01:17:17,791
I'm taking her with me.

883
01:17:20,171 --> 01:17:23,197
[Groans]

884
01:17:23,274 --> 01:17:26,937
- You're not taking her anywhere.
- I'll send her back to you.

885
01:17:27,011 --> 01:17:29,479
You just tell me
which piece you want first.

886
01:17:29,547 --> 01:17:32,641
Aah!

887
01:17:32,716 --> 01:17:37,312
Ow! Oh, shit!
[Groaning]

888
01:17:37,388 --> 01:17:39,788
Damn it.

889
01:17:39,857 --> 01:17:42,655
Alex!

890
01:17:45,563 --> 01:17:47,497
[Gasps]

891
01:17:54,905 --> 01:17:57,499
Oh. My God.

892
01:17:57,575 --> 01:17:59,839
What have you done?

893
01:17:59,910 --> 01:18:04,745
[Sobbing]
What have you d-done?

894
01:18:04,815 --> 01:18:07,511
[Sirens Wailing In Distance]

895
01:18:07,651 --> 01:18:11,678
[Woman] Residents of this normally
quiet suburb are still in shock...

896
01:18:11,755 --> 01:18:15,054
as news of the shooting of Gary
Soneji. America's most-wanted man.

897
01:18:15,125 --> 01:18:17,059
Filtered through
their community.

898
01:18:17,127 --> 01:18:19,459
Apparently, Soneji had attempted
to confront, or even harm...

899
01:18:19,530 --> 01:18:22,055
members of the kidnapping
task force hunting him.

900
01:18:22,132 --> 01:18:26,398
So. He came after Jezzie
as payback for Dimitri.

901
01:18:27,872 --> 01:18:30,363
Ostensibly. Yeah.

902
01:18:30,441 --> 01:18:32,375
That's how you want it
on record?

903
01:18:32,443 --> 01:18:35,207
Yeah. For now.

904
01:18:39,617 --> 01:18:41,744
Here they come.

905
01:18:50,127 --> 01:18:54,029
Dr. Cross. Tell me you have at least
an idea where my little girl is.

906
01:18:54,098 --> 01:18:57,192
I'm sorry. Sir. I can't.

907
01:18:57,268 --> 01:18:59,736
You kill the one man
who has the answers.

908
01:18:59,803 --> 01:19:03,534
And you're telling me
you haven't a clue. Not one clue?

909
01:19:03,607 --> 01:19:06,735
The man walked in the fucking room.
And you shot him.

910
01:19:06,810 --> 01:19:08,607
Senator...

911
01:19:08,679 --> 01:19:11,307
standing in his shoes. I'd have
done the same thing. Sir.

912
01:19:11,382 --> 01:19:15,512
That's your job. Not his. He's
supposed to find my little girl.

913
01:19:15,586 --> 01:19:18,749
Not shoot the man
who knows where she is.

914
01:19:18,822 --> 01:19:20,756
[MacArthur]
Senator.

915
01:19:27,131 --> 01:19:29,065
It's not over.

916
01:19:31,335 --> 01:19:34,827
The book is not closed.

917
01:19:55,426 --> 01:19:57,360
Alex...

918
01:19:59,997 --> 01:20:02,295
thank you
for saving my life.

919
01:20:02,366 --> 01:20:04,300
Good-bye. Jezzie.

920
01:20:11,842 --> 01:20:14,811
- Wanna hear something funny. Mac?
- Sure.

921
01:20:14,878 --> 01:20:18,541
Cheer me up.

922
01:20:18,616 --> 01:20:22,552
I congratulated Soneji
on scoring $ 12 million.

923
01:20:22,620 --> 01:20:24,679
You mean ten million.

924
01:20:26,590 --> 01:20:29,024
Exactly.

925
01:20:29,093 --> 01:20:33,120
He had no idea
what I was talking about.

926
01:20:47,645 --> 01:20:49,670
[Door Opens]

927
01:20:57,121 --> 01:21:00,249
I know you.
You work at my school.

928
01:21:01,625 --> 01:21:03,559
Eat your food. Megan.

929
01:21:10,134 --> 01:21:13,035
[Door Closes, Locks]

930
01:21:28,152 --> 01:21:30,347
[Watch Beeps]

931
01:21:32,022 --> 01:21:33,956
[Watch Beeps]

932
01:21:44,568 --> 01:21:46,502
[Watch Beeps]

933
01:21:50,908 --> 01:21:53,433
Alex.
Where is this going?

934
01:22:00,617 --> 01:22:04,144
We've been through these tapes
backwards and forwards.

935
01:22:04,221 --> 01:22:06,416
I can't see how this is
helping us find Megan.

936
01:22:09,226 --> 01:22:11,751
You know
what I see, Mac?

937
01:22:11,829 --> 01:22:15,162
Someone was onto Soneji
long before we ever heard of him.

938
01:22:15,232 --> 01:22:17,496
Look at this.
What do you see?

939
01:22:17,568 --> 01:22:20,162
Agent Devine hauling ass
out to the front gate.

940
01:22:20,237 --> 01:22:23,866
Mac. He could have shut this
whole place down from right there.

941
01:22:23,941 --> 01:22:27,308
Now. You wanna tell me
why he didn't?

942
01:22:30,380 --> 01:22:34,578
[Quietly] Good God.
Devine was in on it with him.

943
01:22:34,651 --> 01:22:37,381
Then. When Soneji hit the embassy.
He pulled a double cross.

944
01:22:37,454 --> 01:22:39,388
He ran his own ransom.

945
01:22:39,456 --> 01:22:42,823
No. Soneji was a loner.

946
01:22:42,893 --> 01:22:44,952
An accomplice would have
been beneath him.

947
01:22:45,028 --> 01:22:47,690
I'll tell you
what happened.

948
01:22:47,765 --> 01:22:50,495
Soneji was hoodwinked.

949
01:22:52,236 --> 01:22:55,015
And so were we.

950
01:22:55,148 --> 01:22:58,549
Details are still emerging.
But this much is clear:

951
01:22:58,619 --> 01:23:02,020
The manunt that began over a
week ago in the natiors capitol...

952
01:23:02,089 --> 01:23:04,387
- came to a violent end yesterday,
- [Clattering]

953
01:23:04,458 --> 01:23:07,222
With the death of kidnapper,
Gary Soneji.

954
01:23:40,227 --> 01:23:42,388
[Jezzie]
Don't move.

955
01:23:42,462 --> 01:23:45,158
Turn around.
Hands on the wall. Feet apart.

956
01:23:45,232 --> 01:23:47,166
Hi. Jez.
Where'd you come from?

957
01:23:47,234 --> 01:23:50,101
You know something. Devine.
You're pretty stupid.

958
01:23:50,170 --> 01:23:52,104
Your car in the driveway.

959
01:23:52,172 --> 01:23:55,573
TV so loud. You wouldn't be able
to hear a SWAT team come in.

960
01:23:55,642 --> 01:23:58,133
- What are you doing...
- Shut up!

961
01:24:04,484 --> 01:24:06,611
[Both Laughing]

962
01:24:14,394 --> 01:24:16,658
Where's Megan?

963
01:24:16,730 --> 01:24:19,597
She's in the barn.
She was so doped up.

964
01:24:19,666 --> 01:24:21,861
I don't think she knew
I took her off the boat.

965
01:24:21,935 --> 01:24:24,995
She's still alive? You were
supposed to dump her in the river...

966
01:24:25,072 --> 01:24:29,202
- after you got the diamonds.
- Yeah. Well.

967
01:24:29,276 --> 01:24:33,269
Maybe killing a kid is something
I'm not prepared to do on my own.

968
01:24:33,346 --> 01:24:36,144
Anyway. Today. Tomorrow. It's still
gonna look like Soneji killed her.

969
01:24:36,216 --> 01:24:39,151
She can't die
after Soneji. You idiot.

970
01:24:39,219 --> 01:24:42,677
It doesn't make any difference.
They're never gonna find the body.

971
01:24:47,427 --> 01:24:51,454
Okay. I'll go do it now.
Will that make you happy?

972
01:24:51,531 --> 01:24:55,661
Yeah. It would. Wait!

973
01:24:59,306 --> 01:25:01,399
