received information...

1212
01:56:49,642 --> 01:56:52,167
that senior F.B.I.
And Secret Service officials...

1213
01:56:52,245 --> 01:56:55,112
have arrived at the family home
of Senator Rose.

1214
01:56:55,181 --> 01:56:58,981
We will go there live as soon
as we have our satellite feed.

1215
01:56:59,051 --> 01:57:02,145
Technicians are setting up extra
telephone lines in the Rose home,

1216
01:57:02,221 --> 01:57:04,212
all in preparation
should the kidnapper...

1217
01:57:23,309 --> 01:57:26,801
[Child Groaning]

1218
01:57:27,880 --> 01:57:30,713
[Groaning Continues]

1219
01:57:42,361 --> 01:57:44,352
Mom...

1220
01:57:45,465 --> 01:57:49,959
please.
I just wanna go home.

1221
01:57:50,036 --> 01:57:54,132
The F.B.I. And police are on the
lookout for this man. Gary Soneji.

1222
01:57:54,207 --> 01:57:56,971
- This is a recent photograph...
- We only know that he has...

1223
01:57:57,043 --> 01:58:00,035
disappeared with the 12-year-old
daughter of Senator Hank Rose.

1224
01:58:00,112 --> 01:58:02,046
How and why is on the minds...

1225
01:58:02,114 --> 01:58:04,708
Police are trying to find out
who this man really is,

1226
01:58:04,784 --> 01:58:08,777
his motives for killing
teacher Amy Masterson...

1227
01:58:08,855 --> 01:58:10,789
- [Phone Ringing]
- We go back live to join...

1228
01:58:10,857 --> 01:58:13,018
reporter Alison Peretsky,
who has been at the scene...

1229
01:58:13,092 --> 01:58:15,287
since law enforcement
officials arrived.

1230
01:58:16,596 --> 01:58:20,123
[Reporter Continues,
Indistinct]

1231
01:58:20,199 --> 01:58:24,693
- Yeah?
- [Megan] Mom...

1232
01:58:24,770 --> 01:58:29,639
please.
I wanna go home.

1233
01:58:29,709 --> 01:58:31,802
Hello?

1234
01:58:34,614 --> 01:58:36,548
You tuned into me.
Dr. Cross?

1235
01:58:36,616 --> 01:58:42,179
[Distorted Voice] Sounds like
Alison Peretsky at WNKW Action News.

1236
01:58:42,255 --> 01:58:45,884
- Gary Soneji?
- That'll do for now.

1237
01:58:48,828 --> 01:58:51,262
How'd you get this number?

1238
01:58:51,330 --> 01:58:54,822
Unlisted numbers? Come on. Alex.
There's no such thing.

1239
01:58:54,901 --> 01:58:58,098
It's all out there in the air. You
just have to know how to grab it.

1240
01:58:58,170 --> 01:59:01,731
Hey. How do you feel about
my kidnapping being bigger news...

1241
01:59:01,807 --> 01:59:04,503
than your little tragedy
with Jim Gelway?

1242
01:59:04,577 --> 01:59:08,673
You ought to give an interview
about what happened that night.

1243
01:59:08,748 --> 01:59:13,344
You know what they say about sharing
your pain. It's very cathartic.

1244
01:59:13,419 --> 01:59:18,356
- Thanks. But I'm doing okay.
- That's good to hear. Very good.

1245
01:59:18,424 --> 01:59:21,188
I thought for a while there
you wouldn't be able to get...

1246
01:59:21,260 --> 01:59:24,195
your act back together.
And that would be a great shame.

1247
01:59:24,263 --> 01:59:27,994
I've been planning for a long.
Long time to involve you...

1248
01:59:28,067 --> 01:59:31,195
in the fate of our
little Miss Muffet.

1249
01:59:31,270 --> 01:59:35,570
Megan. Do you have trouble
saying her name?

1250
01:59:35,641 --> 01:59:38,269
[Laughing]

1251
01:59:38,344 --> 01:59:43,043
First-name rapport?
Hostage negotiations 101?

1252
01:59:43,115 --> 01:59:45,606
Now come on. Alex. You can do
better than that. Can't you?

1253
01:59:45,685 --> 01:59:50,122
You think you're gonna dissect me
in three blinks of an eye?

1254
01:59:50,189 --> 01:59:52,419
I'm not that easy.

1255
01:59:52,491 --> 01:59:56,018
But with a little patience
and a little help.

1256
01:59:56,095 --> 01:59:59,087
You just might
profile me to a "T."

1257
01:59:59,165 --> 02:00:02,259
What makes you think
I'm interested?

1258
02:00:04,270 --> 02:00:08,934
They say that when I die.
The case will die.

1259
02:00:09,008 --> 02:00:12,444
They say it'll be
like a book I close.

1260
02:00:12,511 --> 02:00:16,675
But the book.
It will never close.

1261
02:00:18,884 --> 02:00:21,751
Very poetic.
What the hell is it?

1262
02:00:23,222 --> 02:00:27,716
I've left something for your visit
with the Roses tonight.

1263
02:00:28,728 --> 02:00:30,662
You'll find it in your cold.

1264
02:00:30,730 --> 02:00:35,326
Corrugated mailbox.

1265
02:00:35,401 --> 02:00:39,337
Time to get back to work.
Dr. Cross.

1266
02:01:26,452 --> 02:01:29,444
[Soneji's Taped Voice.
Indistinct]

1267
02:01:32,725 --> 02:01:36,821
[Alex On Tape] Megan. Do you
have trouble saying the name?

1268
02:01:36,896 --> 02:01:38,887
[Turns Off Recorder]

1269
02:01:47,440 --> 02:01:49,931
[Chattering]

1270
02:01:51,744 --> 02:01:54,042
Sorry. Detective.
This is a federal case.

1271
02:01:56,515 --> 02:01:58,506
I've been invited.

1272
02:02:00,486 --> 02:02:03,614
We have a detective who may have
evidence pertinent to the case.

1273
02:02:03,689 --> 02:02:05,680
- What should we do about it?
- Alex?

1274
02:02:07,326 --> 02:02:09,317
Special Agent Craig.
Well. I'll be.

1275
02:02:11,464 --> 02:02:13,625
Dare I ask?

1276
02:02:15,701 --> 02:02:18,192
- In my mailbox.
- Anything else?

1277
02:02:20,106 --> 02:02:22,836
That'll get you inside.

1278
02:02:25,010 --> 02:02:29,208
Terry.
Get this to MacArthur.

1279
02:02:29,281 --> 02:02:31,215
Who's in charge?

1280
02:02:31,283 --> 02:02:33,217
Ollie MacArthur.
Pedigree "Feebie."

1281
02:02:33,285 --> 02:02:36,379
Made his bones busting
wackos in the Seattle office.

1282
02:02:36,455 --> 02:02:38,446
Soneji. Clean?

1283
02:02:38,524 --> 02:02:42,221
Clean? Squeaky. Fibers look
generic. Fingerprints. Nada.

1284
02:02:42,294 --> 02:02:45,127
The whole school's
a goddamn forensic vacuum.

1285
02:02:45,197 --> 02:02:49,497
All he left us was one
very neatly strangled teacher.

1286
02:02:49,568 --> 02:02:51,593
Heads are gonna roll
with the Secret Service.

1287
02:02:54,006 --> 02:02:59,069
Oh. Jezzie Flannigan.
Alex Cross.

1288
02:02:59,145 --> 02:03:02,114
Agent Flannigan was in charge of the
Secret Service detail at Cathedral.

1289
02:03:02,181 --> 02:03:04,115
- Dr. Cross.
- Agent Flannigan.

1290
02:03:04,183 --> 02:03:06,515
I've read your books
on profiling.

1291
02:03:06,585 --> 02:03:08,450
Obviously.
Not close enough. But...

1292
02:03:08,450 --> 02:03:09,439
Obviously.
Not close enough. But...

1293
02:03:11,220 --> 02:03:16,021
Kyle, this shoe was I.D. 'd
by the Roses. It's Megars.

1294
02:03:16,091 --> 02:03:18,559
Dr. Alex Cross.
Special agent in charge...

1295
02:03:18,627 --> 02:03:20,595
- Oliver MacArthur.
- How do you do. Sir.

1296
02:03:20,662 --> 02:03:23,062
Alex. I'll catch you later.

1297
02:03:23,132 --> 02:03:25,498
- Forensics.
- Yes. Sir.

1298
02:03:25,567 --> 02:03:28,195
Senator and Mrs. Rose
are through here.

1299
02:03:28,270 --> 02:03:33,435
Before we talk to them. You any
idea why Soneji is involving you?

1300
02:03:33,509 --> 02:03:36,842
- Not at all.
- This way.

1301
02:03:36,912 --> 02:03:40,746
Uh. Excuse me. Shouldn't Agent
Flannigan be in the room with us?

1302
02:03:40,816 --> 02:03:43,580
Not a good idea.
Miss Flannigan is not welcome.

1303
02:03:43,652 --> 02:03:46,280
But she's
a material witness.

1304
02:03:46,355 --> 02:03:50,223
She failed the Roses.
And she failed the Service.

1305
02:03:50,292 --> 02:03:52,419
I think Agent MacArthur
has a point.

1306
02:03:52,494 --> 02:03:55,122
No. He's missing
the point.

1307
02:03:55,197 --> 02:03:58,291
You saw Soneji every day.
Five days a week. For how long?

1308
02:03:58,367 --> 02:04:00,699
Two years.

1309
02:04:00,769 --> 02:04:04,261
You have no idea how much
you know about this case.

1310
02:04:10,279 --> 02:04:12,338
Agent Flannigan.

1311
02:04:16,151 --> 02:04:20,451
They say that when I die.
The case will die.

1312
02:04:20,522 --> 02:04:24,253
They say it'll be
like a book I close.

1313
02:04:24,326 --> 02:04:28,660
But the book,
it will never close.

1314
02:04:28,730 --> 02:04:31,096
[Alex On Tape]
Very poetic. What the hell is it?

1315
02:04:31,166 --> 02:04:34,966
[Soneji] I've left you
something for your visit...

1316
02:04:35,037 --> 02:04:37,028
with the Roses tonight.

1317
02:04:37,105 --> 02:04:42,065
You'll find it in your cold,
corrugated mailbox.

1318
02:04:42,144 --> 02:04:44,135
[Recorder Clicks Off]

1319
02:04:47,516 --> 02:04:51,008
Well. For what it's won'th.
That's Soneji.

1320
02:04:51,086 --> 02:04:53,953
His speech patterrs
the same.

1321
02:04:54,022 --> 02:04:57,958
Is he. Um...

1322
02:04:58,026 --> 02:05:01,189
Are we dealing with
a sex maniac?

1323
02:05:01,263 --> 02:05:04,790
Someone who might,
you know...

1324
02:05:05,801 --> 02:05:08,031
No. Sir.

1325
02:05:08,103 --> 02:05:10,594
This man has no such interest
in your daughter.

1326
02:05:10,672 --> 02:05:12,867
She's merely a means
to an end.

1327
02:05:12,941 --> 02:05:15,136
What do you mean?

1328
02:05:15,210 --> 02:05:19,943
I see no standard procedure
in anything he's done.

1329
02:05:20,015 --> 02:05:22,006
I disagree.
This is a professional kidnapping.

1330
02:05:22,084 --> 02:05:25,110
It's going to be about money.
Which is good.

1331
02:05:26,455 --> 02:05:28,855
But you're saying
it isn't about money.

1332
02:05:31,526 --> 02:05:33,619
I think he wants to
draw this out.

1333
02:05:35,197 --> 02:05:38,132
From what he said,
whatever his motives...

1334
02:05:40,836 --> 02:05:43,805
it's very unusual.

1335
02:05:46,808 --> 02:05:48,742
What did he mean
about the book?

1336
02:05:48,810 --> 02:05:51,301
That it will never close?

1337
02:05:54,549 --> 02:05:56,744
I honestly don't know.

1338
02:05:56,818 --> 02:05:59,480
Well. I think I do.

1339
02:06:01,590 --> 02:06:05,651
Let me tell you
what this Gary Soneji is up to.

1340
02:06:05,727 --> 02:06:09,356
The last thing he wants
is good crisis management.

1341
02:06:09,431 --> 02:06:12,264
What he wants is to confuse.
Rancor.

1342
02:06:12,334 --> 02:06:15,735
Mixed signals, disorientation,
those are his tools.

1343
02:06:15,804 --> 02:06:18,329
So. He calls a local cop.

1344
02:06:18,407 --> 02:06:22,207
A damaged cop, shouldering
some heavy baggage.

1345
02:06:22,277 --> 02:06:24,711
He's using Dr. Cross
as his messenger...

1346
02:06:24,780 --> 02:06:27,874
Excuse me. The man that kidnapped
our daughter didn't call you.

1347
02:06:27,950 --> 02:06:29,884
So your agenda is what?

1348
02:06:29,952 --> 02:06:34,412
- To insult the man he did call?
- Mrs. Rose. I never intended...

1349
02:06:34,489 --> 02:06:37,754
No, you wait a second.
A madman has our daughter,

1350
02:06:37,826 --> 02:06:41,023
and for some reason
he contacted this man.

1351
02:06:41,096 --> 02:06:44,065
Do you know why?

1352
02:06:45,834 --> 02:06:49,235
No. Ma'am. Not yet.

1353
02:07:26,241 --> 02:07:28,675
Hello.

1354
02:07:28,744 --> 02:07:30,905
You okay?

1355
02:07:32,547 --> 02:07:35,539
You. Uh...

1356
02:07:37,252 --> 02:07:40,312
got any tips
for helpless situations?

1357
02:07:42,290 --> 02:07:44,451
Well. You could
smoke a can'ton a day.

1358
02:07:46,328 --> 02:07:48,956
Or you could bounce back.

1359
02:07:49,031 --> 02:07:52,694
Yeah. Well. I don't see
anywhere to bounce to.

1360
02:07:52,768 --> 02:07:55,134
Like to get out of here?

1361
02:08:03,111 --> 02:08:06,547
Can I ask you something?

1362
02:08:06,615 --> 02:08:08,606
Sure.

1363
02:08:11,520 --> 02:08:15,547
What did MacArthur mean
when he referred to you as damaged?

1364
02:08:18,860 --> 02:08:22,352
Last summer. I let a sting operation
get out of control.

1365
02:08:24,199 --> 02:08:26,531
My partner was killed.

1366
02:08:30,605 --> 02:08:32,505
[Whistling]

1367
02:08:41,650 --> 02:08:45,518
Hello. Megan.
How are you?

1368
02:08:45,587 --> 02:08:48,750
Coming to see you.

1369
02:08:48,824 --> 02:08:50,815
Do you recognize my voice?

1370
02:08:53,929 --> 02:08:56,921
It's me.

1371
02:08:56,998 --> 02:08:59,728
Mr. Soneji. Hmm?

1372
02:09:01,970 --> 02:09:04,768
I brought you that.
A lovely cup of tea with honey.

1373
02:09:04,840 --> 02:09:07,741
I know your throat is sore.
It'll make you feel better.

1374
02:09:07,809 --> 02:09:11,609
There you go.
It's all right.

1375
02:09:14,449 --> 02:09:16,383
You have nothing
to be scared of. Megan.

1376
02:09:16,451 --> 02:09:19,443
I'm not scared.

1377
02:09:19,521 --> 02:09:25,255
Good. But you're wondering
what's going on.

1378
02:09:25,327 --> 02:09:29,559
I know what's going on. You're a
kidnapper. And you're a sick weirdo.

1379
02:09:29,631 --> 02:09:32,998
[Laughing]

1380
02:09:33,068 --> 02:09:36,629
Megan. You're the most
opinionated girl in my class.

1381
02:09:36,705 --> 02:09:40,141
- Think you got that from your mom?
- I wanna go home.

1382
02:09:40,208 --> 02:09:44,542
You will. Just promise me
you're going to behave yourself.

1383
02:09:44,613 --> 02:09:49,414
Okay?
So. Now listen.

1384
02:09:49,484 --> 02:09:53,284
If you need to use the bathroom
or anything. Just press that. Okay?

1385
02:09:53,355 --> 02:09:56,290
I wanna go home! Now!

1386
02:09:56,358 --> 02:09:58,952
- I brought you some fresh clothes.
- Please!

1387
02:09:59,027 --> 02:10:02,136
Mr. Soneji. Please!

1388
02:10:02,270 --> 02:10:04,170
[Gun Clicks]

1389
02:10:04,238 --> 02:10:06,729
This is a fine gun.

1390
02:10:06,808 --> 02:10:11,575
It's Turkish.
Handmade. 1924.

1391
02:10:11,646 --> 02:10:13,807
That is nice.

1392
02:10:13,881 --> 02:10:16,873
My daddy won it in a game
of poker. Aces and eights.

1393
02:10:16,951 --> 02:10:20,318
Dead mars hand.

1394
02:10:20,388 --> 02:10:23,516
That's about as much
as I know about my father.

1395
02:10:23,591 --> 02:10:26,082
Have a seat.

1396
02:10:31,899 --> 02:10:35,995
Do you know of any relationship
between Amy Masterson and Soneji?

1397
02:10:36,070 --> 02:10:40,234
Amy? No way.
Why do you ask?

1398
02:10:40,308 --> 02:10:43,675
He strangled her.

1399
02:10:43,745 --> 02:10:46,612
It's an act of passion.

1400
02:10:46,681 --> 02:10:49,616
It's a demonstration
of will.

1401
02:10:49,684 --> 02:10:52,175
A message.

1402
02:10:53,554 --> 02:10:56,352
Take me seriously.
What do you see?

1403
02:10:56,424 --> 02:10:59,359
- Dr. Cross...
- Alex.

1404
02:10:59,427 --> 02:11:02,726
Alex. Womars intuition.
Third eye. Sixth sense...

1405
02:11:02,797 --> 02:11:04,731
whatever it is.
I don't have it.

1406
02:11:04,799 --> 02:11:06,858
Sure you do. You just
don't look at it right.

1407
02:11:06,934 --> 02:11:08,925
Every face has two aspects.

1408
02:11:09,003 --> 02:11:12,632
Now try looking at it down
the middle. One side at a time.

1409
02:11:12,707 --> 02:11:15,073
Would you say this man
was confident?

1410
02:11:15,143 --> 02:11:17,976
- Yeah.
- Narcissistic?

1411
02:11:18,046 --> 02:11:22,380
- L-I wouldn't know.
- Ever see any flashes of hatred?

1412
02:11:22,450 --> 02:11:25,817
- No. No. No!
- Anger? Hostility?

1413
02:11:25,887 --> 02:11:30,324
Look. Everything about him
was right.

1414
02:11:30,391 --> 02:11:34,555
He was always patient. He was
pleasant. He had a sense of humor.

1415
02:11:34,629 --> 02:11:37,962
I mean. He was
the perfect teacher.

1416
02:11:42,870 --> 02:11:44,838
What do you see?

1417
02:11:47,208 --> 02:11:49,176
I see...

1418
02:11:49,243 --> 02:11:51,643
No. I mean about me.

1419
02:11:53,281 --> 02:11:55,909
What do you see about me?

1420
02:11:55,983 --> 02:11:58,952
That's why you're here.
Isn't it?

1421
02:11:59,020 --> 02:12:04,925
Size me up. Evaluate
your primary material witness?

1422
02:12:08,396 --> 02:12:11,024
I see that you're about
to start an argument.

1423
02:12:11,099 --> 02:12:12,964
I need to help get her back.

1424
02:12:13,034 --> 02:12:14,797
What makes you think
I want a partner?

1425
02:12:14,869 --> 02:12:17,167
- You don't. I can understand that.
- That's right.

1426
02:12:17,238 --> 02:12:20,366
- No. You can't.
- Can I tell you why I don't care?

1427
02:12:23,311 --> 02:12:25,245
Shoot.

1428
02:12:28,583 --> 02:12:33,748
Look. When I was
assigned to Cathedral.

1429
02:12:33,821 --> 02:12:35,812
It was a job
I didn't want.

1430
02:12:35,890 --> 02:12:39,519
It's a far cry from working
rope lines or flying Air Force One.

1431
02:12:39,594 --> 02:12:43,121
But I have been there
for three years.

1432
02:12:43,197 --> 02:12:46,997
I have been responsible
for Megan for three years.

1433
02:12:47,068 --> 02:12:50,231
And that little girl means
more to me than even a partner.

1434
02:12:50,304 --> 02:12:52,966
Can you understand that?

1435
02:12:55,343 --> 02:12:57,743
I suppose so.

1436
02:12:59,514 --> 02:13:04,144
Even if I say no. You'll probably
follow me around wherever I go.

1437
02:13:06,487 --> 02:13:10,321
So. If it's a choice between
having you as a partner...

1438
02:13:10,391 --> 02:13:16,057
or as a stalker. I guess I'll
take my chances with a partner.

1439
02:13:18,232 --> 02:13:20,166
Thank you.

1440
02:13:31,579 --> 02:13:34,912
The student drop-off is there.
That's my morning post.

1441
02:13:34,982 --> 02:13:39,976
Students sign in. Cameras are
there. There. There and there.

1442
02:13:40,054 --> 02:13:42,545
Motions sensors
all around the periphery.

1443
02:13:44,192 --> 02:13:47,389
Foolproof way to keep
the kooks out.

1444
02:13:47,461 --> 02:13:51,659
Exactly. We were always looking
in the wrong direction.

1445
02:13:51,732 --> 02:13:54,530
- Which door did he go out?
- Uh. That one there.

1446
02:13:54,602 --> 02:13:57,264
It's a straight shot
to his parking space.

1447
02:14:01,008 --> 02:14:02,999
Let's go in.

1448
02:14:10,218 --> 02:14:13,312
- His classroom.
- Mm-hmm.

1449
02:14:13,387 --> 02:14:17,721
He was teaching how everything
on the Internet is connected.

