02:23:49,019 --> 02:23:52,250
Evening.
What's the problem?

1550
02:23:52,322 --> 02:23:55,018
Help! Help me!

1551
02:23:55,091 --> 02:23:58,583
You've got a rule 21 problem...
no running lights.

1552
02:23:59,763 --> 02:24:03,269
Again. I just replaced
the fuses yesterday.

1553
02:24:03,403 --> 02:24:06,099
Help! Help!

1554
02:24:06,172 --> 02:24:09,767
Sir. No running lights.
You're gonna have to follow us in.

1555
02:24:09,842 --> 02:24:12,538
Help!
Please. Help me!

1556
02:24:12,612 --> 02:24:15,581
Well. Let me see what I can do
with the fuse box.

1557
02:24:15,648 --> 02:24:17,513
Hold on. Hold on.

1558
02:24:20,386 --> 02:24:24,516
I'm in here! Help me!
I'm in here. Help!

1559
02:24:24,590 --> 02:24:27,150
Help! Help!

1560
02:24:36,936 --> 02:24:39,666
How's that?

1561
02:24:41,240 --> 02:24:43,708
Thanks a lot. Fellas.

1562
02:24:46,479 --> 02:24:51,178
Help!
Help me. Please!

1563
02:25:01,327 --> 02:25:05,593
[Sobbing]
Help me. Please!

1564
02:25:05,665 --> 02:25:07,929
Help me!

1565
02:25:14,574 --> 02:25:17,407
"And before the hood
was pulled over his head.

1566
02:25:17,477 --> 02:25:20,935
"He bragged
to his executioner.

1567
02:25:21,013 --> 02:25:24,414
"'They think that when I die.
The case will die.

1568
02:25:24,484 --> 02:25:27,920
"'They think it will be
like a book I close.

1569
02:25:27,987 --> 02:25:31,684
'But the book.
It will never close."'

1570
02:25:33,426 --> 02:25:39,126
Soneji was quoting the final words
of Richard Bruno Hauptman.

1571
02:25:41,234 --> 02:25:43,293
I'm sorry.
I don't follow.

1572
02:25:43,369 --> 02:25:47,635
1932. The infant son
of Charles Lindbergh.

1573
02:25:47,707 --> 02:25:50,835
America's greatest hero.
Was kidnapped.

1574
02:25:50,910 --> 02:25:54,869
When Bruno Hauptman was arrested,
what followed became known as...

1575
02:25:54,947 --> 02:25:56,881
"the crime of the century."

1576
02:25:56,949 --> 02:25:59,645
I believe that Soneji
wants to do the same thing.

1577
02:25:59,719 --> 02:26:02,620
You think we're dealing
with a copycat.

1578
02:26:02,688 --> 02:26:05,248
Something like that.

1579
02:26:05,324 --> 02:26:07,758
Dr. Cross...

1580
02:26:07,827 --> 02:26:10,990
what does he want
from you?

1581
02:26:15,601 --> 02:26:18,661
He's brought me in
and left this trail...

1582
02:26:18,738 --> 02:26:23,801
because he wants me to make sure
that he's properly appreciated.

1583
02:26:24,911 --> 02:26:27,379
But in order for him
to achieve this...

1584
02:26:29,916 --> 02:26:31,850
he has to kill Megan.

1585
02:26:31,918 --> 02:26:35,354
No. No.
Not necessarily.

1586
02:26:35,421 --> 02:26:38,549
The death of the Lindbergh baby
was accidental.

1587
02:26:38,624 --> 02:26:41,855
Nevertheless. It's critical
that we pull his strings.

1588
02:26:41,928 --> 02:26:43,919
The more we make him
a living legend.

1589
02:26:43,996 --> 02:26:45,987
The more likely he is
to keep Megan alive.

1590
02:26:46,065 --> 02:26:48,260
[Man] Dr. Cross,
you've been brought into this case,

1591
02:26:48,334 --> 02:26:50,393
what can you tell us
about Gary Soneji?

1592
02:26:50,469 --> 02:26:53,336
I can tell you that Soneji
is very determined.

1593
02:26:53,406 --> 02:26:57,706
Obviously highly capable and we
consider him a serious adversary.

1594
02:26:57,777 --> 02:26:59,938
[Reporter]
What about Megan Rose?

1595
02:27:00,012 --> 02:27:02,981
[Cross] Megan Rose
is Gary Soneji's ace.

1596
02:27:03,049 --> 02:27:06,177
As long as he has her,
he's in control.

1597
02:27:06,252 --> 02:27:08,686
[Clattering]

1598
02:27:18,464 --> 02:27:21,194
Sir, would you assign
as many agents to this case...

1599
02:27:21,267 --> 02:27:23,132
if she wasrt
a senator's daughter?

1600
02:27:23,202 --> 02:27:25,636
The size of our task force
is a reflection...

1601
02:27:25,705 --> 02:27:28,731
of who Gary Soneji is.
Not Megan Rose.

1602
02:27:29,909 --> 02:27:32,070
- [Buzzes]
- Mr. Soneji.

1603
02:27:32,144 --> 02:27:34,078
[Cross] You can parse
the words if you'd like...

1604
02:27:34,146 --> 02:27:35,875
Hello?

1605
02:27:35,948 --> 02:27:38,246
I need to
go to the bathroom.

1606
02:27:38,317 --> 02:27:41,081
All right.
Be right there.

1607
02:27:48,394 --> 02:27:50,362
[Door Opens]

1608
02:28:04,010 --> 02:28:06,342
[Coughs]

1609
02:28:38,778 --> 02:28:42,077
- [Quietly] Come on.
- [Typing]

1610
02:28:47,820 --> 02:28:51,620
- Come on.
- [Hisses]

1611
02:29:07,373 --> 02:29:09,568
Hey!

1612
02:29:16,282 --> 02:29:18,842
Help!

1613
02:29:20,219 --> 02:29:22,517
Please. Help!

1614
02:29:23,889 --> 02:29:26,915
Help! Please!

1615
02:29:26,992 --> 02:29:29,017
- Help!
- ## [Walkman. Indistinct]

1616
02:29:36,435 --> 02:29:40,132
Help! Please!

1617
02:29:40,206 --> 02:29:42,606
Help me! Please!

