02:30:13,105 --> 02:30:14,868
No. Please!

1627
02:30:16,876 --> 02:30:18,810
[Turns Boat Engine Off]

1628
02:30:19,879 --> 02:30:22,040
[Crying]
Please!

1629
02:30:22,114 --> 02:30:27,051
Please!
Help! Please!

1630
02:30:27,119 --> 02:30:30,418
[Crying]
Please!

1631
02:30:30,489 --> 02:30:34,016
[Coughing]

1632
02:30:34,093 --> 02:30:38,894
Shh. This will keep you warm.
Here you go.

1633
02:30:38,964 --> 02:30:42,092
Megan. You promised me
you were going to behave yourself.

1634
02:30:42,168 --> 02:30:45,660
Because of you. What you've done.
That man is dead.

1635
02:30:47,439 --> 02:30:50,567
Now... promise me.

1636
02:30:50,643 --> 02:30:53,544
Promise me you're going to
be a good little girl. Okay?

1637
02:30:53,612 --> 02:30:55,944
- [Whimpering]
- All right?

1638
02:30:56,015 --> 02:30:58,074
Say. "Yes. Mr. Soneji."

1639
02:30:59,985 --> 02:31:01,919
Say. "Yes. Mr. Soneji."

1640
02:31:01,987 --> 02:31:06,117
Y-Yes. Mr. Soneji.

1641
02:31:06,192 --> 02:31:08,126
Okay.

1642
02:31:10,029 --> 02:31:12,896
Let's go have
that cup of tea.

1643
02:31:48,567 --> 02:31:51,331
I'd say eight hours.
About 9:00 a.m.

1644
02:31:51,403 --> 02:31:54,861
Slugs are large caliber.
Shots hit him here. Here.

1645
02:31:54,940 --> 02:31:56,908
Kill shot tapped him
crown of the head.

1646
02:31:56,975 --> 02:32:01,241
This here is Thomas Mathias.
He found all this. This way.

1647
02:32:12,758 --> 02:32:15,750
[Boat Engine Accelerating]

1648
02:32:35,514 --> 02:32:39,678
She's not in the water. Jezzie.
Soneji still has her.

1649
02:32:39,751 --> 02:32:41,685
There's no way
of knowing that.

1650
02:32:41,753 --> 02:32:44,381
Think about it.
Megan is precious cargo.

1651
02:32:44,456 --> 02:32:47,755
Soneji's not gonna let
some twist of fate bring her harm.

1652
02:32:47,826 --> 02:32:49,760
Right?

1653
02:32:51,963 --> 02:32:54,727
But why Megan?
Why her?

1654
02:33:00,238 --> 02:33:02,172
Come on.

1655
02:33:02,240 --> 02:33:04,174
Where are you going?

1656
02:33:04,242 --> 02:33:06,540
Back to the city.
We'll talk in the car.

1657
02:33:09,648 --> 02:33:11,809
[Cross]
You asked. "Why Megan?"

1658
02:33:11,883 --> 02:33:15,751
That's the question we should have
been asking right from the start:

1659
02:33:15,821 --> 02:33:18,619
Why Megan?

1660
02:33:21,626 --> 02:33:25,153
Who is Senator Hank Rose?

1661
02:33:25,230 --> 02:33:27,790
- He's...
- Nobody.

1662
02:33:29,434 --> 02:33:31,959
Most people don't even know
who he is. Never heard of him.

1663
02:33:32,037 --> 02:33:35,063
Couldrt pick him
out of a lineup.

1664
02:33:35,140 --> 02:33:39,440
This is front-page news now. Where
will it be in two months? Ayear?

1665
02:33:39,511 --> 02:33:43,811
Oblivion.
Know why?

1666
02:33:43,882 --> 02:33:48,615
Because Senator Hank Rose
is no Charles Lindbergh.

1667
02:33:49,688 --> 02:33:51,781
Well. Okay.
Then. Who is?

1668
02:33:51,857 --> 02:33:56,419
Ah. There's
the troublesome question.

1669
02:33:56,495 --> 02:34:02,127
Come on. Jezzie. Two years.
