What?

1686
02:36:11,196 --> 02:36:13,721
Well. MacArthur's
dragnetting the bay. Right?

1687
02:36:13,798 --> 02:36:16,323
And. I mean.
He's not really missing us.

1688
02:36:16,401 --> 02:36:19,165
So I was thinking maybe
we could just stick around and.

1689
02:36:19,237 --> 02:36:22,297
You know. Scope out
the place a bit.

1690
02:36:24,809 --> 02:36:28,745
Agent Flannigan.
Are you...

1691
02:36:28,813 --> 02:36:30,940
are you suggesting
a stakeout here?

1692
02:36:32,317 --> 02:36:34,751
Yeah. You know.
Stale coffee. Some doughnuts.

1693
02:36:34,819 --> 02:36:38,778
No. No. That's a first-class
stakeout. Agent Flannigan.

1694
02:36:38,857 --> 02:36:41,485
What you're talking about
here would be no frills.

1695
02:36:41,560 --> 02:36:44,893
You'd only get to think about
stale coffee and doughnuts.

1696
02:36:46,598 --> 02:36:49,032
Well. I can handle it
if you can.

1697
02:37:46,464 --> 02:37:48,830
I get the feeling
you've done this a lot.

1698
02:37:48,900 --> 02:37:50,891
Oh. Yeah.

1699
02:37:50,969 --> 02:37:52,903
Every chance I get.

1700
02:37:55,173 --> 02:37:58,904
Especially when
it's cold and wet.

1701
02:38:11,189 --> 02:38:14,488
- No parking here.
- We're on the clock. Officer.

1702
02:38:14,559 --> 02:38:17,858
- Everything okay?
- Everything is all right.

1703
02:38:41,586 --> 02:38:43,713
- What's the problem?
- [Gunshots]

1704
02:38:43,788 --> 02:38:45,813
[Groaning]

1705
02:38:47,392 --> 02:38:49,326
[Keys Jingling]

1706
02:38:56,067 --> 02:38:58,627
Go ahead. Jezzie.

1707
02:38:58,703 --> 02:39:00,637
What?

1708
02:39:03,741 --> 02:39:05,834
Have one.

1709
02:39:05,910 --> 02:39:07,844
Thank you.

1710
02:39:36,274 --> 02:39:38,208
[Mumbling]

1711
02:39:39,377 --> 02:39:41,311
[Door Unlocks]

1712
02:39:56,627 --> 02:39:58,788
[Counting In Russian]

1713
02:40:00,999 --> 02:40:03,467
[Continues Counting In Russian]

1714
02:40:07,538 --> 02:40:09,972
[Counting In Russian]

1715
02:40:17,949 --> 02:40:20,281
Alex. That's Dimitri.

1716
02:40:58,356 --> 02:41:00,847
Jezzie. It's him.

1717
02:41:00,925 --> 02:41:04,361
- It's him!
- [Car Engine Starts]

1718
02:41:04,429 --> 02:41:07,626
[Tires Squealing]

1719
02:41:13,237 --> 02:41:16,502
[Tires Squealing]

1720
02:41:23,347 --> 02:41:27,647
Soneji, hold it
right there!

1721
02:41:33,257 --> 02:41:35,555
Jezzie. Shoot the tires!

1722
02:41:36,794 --> 02:41:38,785
- [Tires Squealing]
- Jezzie!

1723
02:41:55,246 --> 02:41:57,806
Jezzie!

1724
02:41:59,584 --> 02:42:02,314
[Yelling In Russian]

1725
02:42:02,386 --> 02:42:04,980
Police! Don't shoot!
Don't shoot!

1726
02:42:07,992 --> 02:42:10,324
[Tires Squealing]

1727
02:42:13,297 --> 02:42:16,994
[Man Speaking Russian]

1728
02:42:17,135 --> 02:42:20,127
[Murmuring]

1729
02:42:20,204 --> 02:42:24,038
[Man Speaking Russian]

1730
02:42:24,108 --> 02:42:26,770
- [Continues In Russian]
- [Dimitri] Jezzie!

1731
02:42:32,650 --> 02:42:35,244
Jezzie. You're gonna
get Megan back. Right?

1732
02:42:35,319 --> 02:42:38,686
Yes. We are.
I promise.

1733
02:42:38,756 --> 02:42:40,747
Use this
to get Mr. Soneji.

1734
02:42:43,060 --> 02:42:45,858
I will. Thank you.

1735
02:42:49,200 --> 02:42:51,794
You talk to Hal.
I want you to bring him up to speed.

1736
02:42:51,869 --> 02:42:53,803
Well done. Guys.

1737
02:42:53,871 --> 02:42:56,032
Avert an international crisis
and paint Soneji into a corner.

1738
02:42:56,107 --> 02:42:58,041
Not bad for a night's work.

1739
02:42:58,109 --> 02:43:01,510
Soneji ditched a patrol car near
Reno Park. Hijacked a tan Sierra.

1740
02:43:01,579 --> 02:43:04,810
One bullet in the driver's head.
Last seen heading toward Route 50.

1741
02:43:04,882 --> 02:43:09,251
Annapolis. I knew it. Seventy-five
thousand boats. Other marinas?

1742
02:43:09,320 --> 02:43:12,653
We're here. Dead fisherman here.
These. All the marinas.

1743
02:43:12,723 --> 02:43:14,816
All locked down.
Patrol boats in each of them.

1744
02:43:14,892 --> 02:43:17,326
All right. Listen up.
We gotta move fast.

1745
02:43:17,395 --> 02:43:20,091
Roadblock Route 50 and triple
the surveillance in the harbors.

1746
02:43:20,164 --> 02:43:23,292
I want two choppers on the pad
in five minutes. Let's go!

1747
02:43:30,441 --> 02:43:32,375
[Grunts]

1748
02:43:52,830 --> 02:43:54,764
[Cocks Gun]

1749
02:44:12,016 --> 02:44:13,950
[Mumbles]

1750
02:44:38,679 --> 02:44:40,613
What's wrong?

1751
02:44:43,984 --> 02:44:46,509
I blew it.
That's what's wrong.

1752
02:44:49,857 --> 02:44:53,293
I had a shot right before
he hit the hydrant.

1753
02:44:53,360 --> 02:44:57,820
But instead of pulling the trigger.
I was thinking. I was thinking.

1754
02:44:57,898 --> 02:45:00,662
Yeah. You were thinking.
About your shot going astray...

1755
02:45:00,734 --> 02:45:02,827
and blowing Soneji's head off.
In which case...

1756
02:45:02,903 --> 02:45:04,837
We would never find Megan.
I know that.

1757
02:45:04,905 --> 02:45:07,465
Well. Then. Don't beat
yourself up for being prudent.

1758
02:45:07,541 --> 02:45:11,136
You don't get it. I was trained
to shoot first and think later.

1759
02:45:11,211 --> 02:45:14,374
Jezzie.
For heavers sake.

1760
02:45:14,448 --> 02:45:16,382
If you hadrt convinced me
to stay there.

1761
02:45:16,450 --> 02:45:18,384
Soneji would have
two victims instead of one.

1762
02:45:18,452 --> 02:45:21,080
Plus we'd have an international
incident on our hands.

1763
02:45:21,155 --> 02:45:25,285
- You did good. You did good.
- Yes. But still...

1764
02:45:27,594 --> 02:45:29,585
- Anything?
- Oh. Not yet.

1765
02:45:29,663 --> 02:45:31,654
We're sitting on the area.

1766
02:45:31,732 --> 02:45:34,724
Chief. Soneji's
on the phone.

1767
02:45:43,811 --> 02:45:46,507
[Beeping]

1768
02:45:46,580 --> 02:45:49,515
- Soneji?
- [Distorted] Detective Cross.

1769
02:45:49,583 --> 02:45:51,847
I want to explain
how the agenda's changed.

1770
02:45:51,919 --> 02:45:55,013
You're gonna bring me
ten million in diamonds.

1771
02:45:55,089 --> 02:45:57,819
Point five carat.
Color "D." clarity Sl-2.

1772
02:45:57,891 --> 02:46:00,724
In a thermos
in nine hours.

1773
02:46:00,794 --> 02:46:04,423
If the stones are rigged, laser
tagged, irradiated, the girl dies.

1774
02:46:04,498 --> 02:46:08,025
- Does that penetrate?
- It does.

1775
02:46:08,102 --> 02:46:12,232
I'll call back.
4:00 p.m. Sharp.

1776
02:46:12,306 --> 02:46:15,002
- [Hangs Up. Dial Tone]
- He beat the trace.

1777
02:46:15,075 --> 02:46:18,772
Clock's ticking, people.
Let's move this downtown. Let's go!

1778
02:46:18,846 --> 02:46:23,249
[Sobbing]

1779
02:46:33,460 --> 02:46:35,394
[Ringing]

1780
02:46:37,765 --> 02:46:40,256
[Ring]

1781
02:46:42,669 --> 02:46:45,160
[Ring]

1782
02:46:47,508 --> 02:46:50,068
- [Distorted Voice] Dr. Cross.
- I'm here.

1783
02:46:50,144 --> 02:46:54,080
The Watergate. 20 minutes.

1784
02:46:54,148 --> 02:46:57,049
- There's a package for Mr. Antwerp.
- [Dial Tone]

1785
02:46:57,117 --> 02:46:59,517
Okay, people, let's move.

1786
02:47:03,056 --> 02:47:05,854
- Don't lose him. Kiddo.
- You won't even see me.

1787
02:47:15,936 --> 02:47:18,962
[Tires Squealing]

1788
02:47:46,433 --> 02:47:49,960
- I'm on police business.
- Eddie. This way.

1789
02:47:59,513 --> 02:48:01,447
Hi. How are you?

1790
02:48:01,515 --> 02:48:03,574
Do you have a package
for Mr. Antwerp?

1791
02:48:03,650 --> 02:48:05,709
Yes.

1792
02:48:09,089 --> 02:48:11,387
Yes. Sir.

1793
02:48:11,458 --> 02:48:15,155
[Phone Ringing]

1794
02:48:15,229 --> 02:48:17,163
Over there. That one.

1795
02:48:19,199 --> 02:48:23,363
[Phone Continues Ringing]

1796
02:48:26,273 --> 02:48:28,207
[Ring]

1797
02:48:28,275 --> 02:48:31,403
- Cross.
- Leave the phone. Leave the car.

1798
02:48:31,478 --> 02:48:35,312
Pennsylvania and Sixth.
The fountain. 14 minutes. Run.

1799
02:48:35,382 --> 02:48:37,850
Thanks.

1800
02:48:37,918 --> 02:48:40,386
- [Cross] Mac. You there?
- Alex.

1801
02:48:40,454 --> 02:48:43,150
He made me ditch the car.
Looks like it's a running game.

1802
02:48:43,223 --> 02:48:46,249
I'm on my way
to Sixth and Pennsylvania.

1803
02:48:48,495 --> 02:48:50,725
I'm left
and behind you, Alex.

1804
02:49:12,152 --> 02:49:14,780
Bearing onto Pennsylvania.

1805
02:49:14,855 --> 02:49:18,052
[Tires Squealing]

1806
02:49:18,125 --> 02:49:21,788
[Ring]

1807
02:49:23,797 --> 02:49:25,731
- [Ring]
- Cross.

1808
02:49:25,799 --> 02:49:29,291
Twelfth and Madison. Twelve minutes
will get you there. Go.

1809
02:49:32,339 --> 02:49:34,864
Unit three.
Ioop on 23rd Street.

1810
02:49:34,942 --> 02:49:37,376
Unit six. Take "K" Street
and double back.

1811
02:49:45,052 --> 02:49:47,418
You've got four units
on top. Alex.

1812
02:49:48,488 --> 02:49:50,581
[Phone Ringing]

1813
02:49:51,725 --> 02:49:54,091
[Ring]

1814
02:49:55,295 --> 02:49:57,559
- [Ring]
- Cross.

1815
02:49:57,631 --> 02:50:01,032
Four minutes. Union Station.
Main entrance.

1816
02:50:02,636 --> 02:50:05,799
Jezzie. Union Station.
Main entrance.

1817
02:50:05,872 --> 02:50:07,806
[Horn Honking]

1818
02:50:09,109 --> 02:50:11,805
It's rush hour.
He's drawing them into a crowd.

1819
02:50:27,894 --> 02:50:31,193
[Phone Ringing]

1820
02:50:33,934 --> 02:50:38,098
[Ringing]

1821
02:50:38,171 --> 02:50:40,833
Hey! Hey!

1822
02:50:40,907 --> 02:50:44,070
Don't answer that!
I think it's for me.

1823
02:50:44,144 --> 02:50:46,908
- Cross.
- [Hangs Up. Dial Tone]

1824
02:50:46,980 --> 02:50:50,381
[Man On P.A.,
Indistinct]

1825
02:50:50,450 --> 02:50:53,146
[Phone Ringing]

1826
02:50:53,220 --> 02:50:55,620
[Ring]

1827
02:50:55,689 --> 02:50:59,090
[Ring]

1828
02:50:59,159 --> 02:51:01,093
[Ring]

1829
02:51:02,162 --> 02:51:04,096
[Ring]

1830
02:51:04,164 --> 02:51:08,066
- Cross.
- Keep this phone. Take the metro.

1831
02:51:08,135 --> 02:51:11,195
Platform "A."
You got two minutes. Go!

1832
02:51:17,744 --> 02:51:21,976
Jezzie. Metro.
Downstairs. Platform "A."

1833
02:51:35,732 --> 02:51:38,098
[Phone Ringing]

1834
02:51:38,168 --> 02:51:41,365
- Cross.
- Go to the center of the platform.

1835
02:52:17,240 --> 02:52:19,936
[Distorted Voice]
Track 15. go!

1836
02:52:42,999 --> 02:52:45,058
[Distorted Voice]
Go to the first car.

1837
02:53:08,024 --> 02:53:10,049
[Distorted Voice]
You there yet?

1838
02:53:10,126 --> 02:53:12,651
- Yeah, I'm there.
- Go to the left side.

1839
02:53:12,729 --> 02:53:16,221
- Open the window.
- These windows don't open.

1840
02:53:16,299 --> 02:53:18,824
You're smart, Detective,
improvise.

1841
02:53:18,902 --> 02:53:20,836
Quickly.

1842
02:53:22,272 --> 02:53:24,331
- Police officer. Everybody. Down!
- [Woman] What?

1843
02:53:24,407 --> 02:53:28,366
- Get down! Everybody. Down!
- Come on, outta my way!

1844
02:53:29,979 --> 02:53:32,072
[Screams. Gasps]

1845
02:53:32,148 --> 02:53:36,585
You ready?
All right. Now. Throw!

1846
02:53:52,502 --> 02:53:55,869
[Chattering]

1847
02:53:56,005 --> 02:53:58,872
We can neither confirm
nor deny that Gary Soneji...

1848
02:53:58,942 --> 02:54:01,877
was involved in the incident
on the MTA train this morning.

1849
02:54:01,945 --> 02:54:03,936
We've heard that a ransom
was paid. Comment?

1850
02:54:04,013 --> 02:54:07,449
- I can't comment on any of that.
- What about Megan Rose?

1851
02:54:07,517 --> 02:54:10,111
I'm not going to go into
any details at this time.

1852
02:54:10,186 --> 02:54:12,211
What about Soneji's
state of mind?

1853
02:54:12,288 --> 02:54:15,223
I'm not going to comment
on his mental stability.

1854
02:54:15,291 --> 02:54:17,555
You can draw
your own conclusions.

1855
02:54:17,627 --> 02:54:22,360
Now, Senator Rose has agreed
to make a statement,

1856
02:54:22,432 --> 02:54:24,627
- So?
- The file on Soneji.

1857
02:54:24,701 --> 02:54:27,670
- Is it still on your kitchen table?
- Yeah. Why?

1858
02:54:27,737 --> 02:54:29,671
I'm gonna have
another look at it.

1859
02:54:29,739 --> 02:54:33,573
This business about the diamonds.
Money. I didn't see it coming.

1860
02:54:33,643 --> 02:54:36,510
[Typing]

1861
02:54:36,579 --> 02:54:39,571
I am grateful that
the F.B.I. Is here.

1862
02:54:39,649 --> 02:54:44,586
With the objective expertise
to find out where my daughter is.

1863
02:54:44,654 --> 02:54:46,588
Secondly, I now...

1864
02:54:52,896 --> 02:54:55,023
[Jezzie]
This is worse than killing time.

1865
02:54:55,098 --> 02:55:00,001
Yeah. But you'd be amazed at how
often the small. Neglected things...

1866
02:55:00,069 --> 02:55:03,368
become the most important.

1867
02:55:03,439 --> 02:55:07,000
I just got the feeling
we're missing something.

1868
02:55:07,076 --> 02:55:10,534
Maybe I'm in
the wrong line of work.

1869
02:55:10,613 --> 02:55:14,049
Maybe I should take on
something less challenging.

1870
02:55:14,117 --> 02:55:16,312
You do what you are.
Jezzie.

1871
02:55:16,386 --> 02:55:19,253
You mean.
You are what you do.

1872
02:55:19,322 --> 02:55:23,224
No. I mean.
You do what you are.

1873
02:55:23,293 --> 02:55:26,626
You're born with a gift.

1874
02:55:26,696 --> 02:55:31,224
If not that. Then you get good
at something along the way.

1875
02:55:31,301 --> 02:55:34,634
And what you're good at.
You don't take for granted.

1876
02:55:34,704 --> 02:55:36,831
You don't betray it.

1877
02:55:39,576 --> 02:55:42,841
What if you do
betray your gift?

1878
02:55:42,912 --> 02:55:47,815
Then. You betray yourself.
That's a sad thing.

1879
02:55:47,884 --> 02:55:50,284
[Siren Wailing In Distance]

1880
02:55:50,353 --> 02:55:52,378
[Knock At Door]

1881
02:55:54,023 --> 02:55:56,856
- Who is it?
- [Man] Police.

1882
02:55:58,394 --> 02:56:00,885
[Electrical Charge]

1883
02:56:05,735 --> 02:56:07,669
Gary Soneji.

1884
02:56:07,737 --> 02:56:10,365
Hi. Alex.

1885
02:56:12,742 --> 02:56:17,577
Now. Right hand. Thumb and
forefinger. Just give me the gun.

1886
02:56:20,450 --> 02:56:24,853
Alex. You can't shoot me.
You'll never find Megan.

1887
02:56:40,303 --> 02:56:42,567
Sit down. Alex.

1888
02:56:50,680 --> 02:56:53,615
I'm-I'm a little concerned. Alex.
I'm a little...

1889
02:56:53,683 --> 02:56:56,277
I'm a little worried
that you...

1890
02:56:56,352 --> 02:56:58,843
you don't really care
to understand me anymore;

1891
02:56:58,921 --> 02:57:01,082
that you won't paint
an accurate portrait.

1892
02:57:01,157 --> 02:57:03,990
And I need you to convince me
that I'm wrong.

1893
02:57:04,060 --> 02:57:07,154
In order to do that. We're going
to have to talk about Megan Rose.

1894
02:57:07,230 --> 02:57:12,327
No. No bargaining. Alex.
No cheap interrogation techniques.

1895
02:57:12,402 --> 02:57:14,893
It's transparent.
And it's clumsy.

1896
02:57:14,971 --> 02:57:17,997
This is between
me and you.

1897
02:57:18,074 --> 02:57:20,702
I want you to see.

1898
02:57:20,777 --> 02:57:26,682
I want you to look inside here
and tell me what the fuck you see!

1899
02:57:28,017 --> 02:57:30,008
I'm a gift to you, Alex.

1900
02:57:30,086 --> 02:57:33,852
I'm a gift to you.

1901
02:57:33,923 --> 02:57:39,190
And you are beyond... pitiful
if you cannot understand that.

1902
02:57:40,596 --> 02:57:43,258
I'm living proof
that a mind...

1903
02:57:44,934 --> 02:57:47,300
the mind is
a terrible thing.

1904
02:57:48,905 --> 02:57:53,933
[Laughing]

1905
02:57:57,980 --> 02:58:00,312
I see you've got
your sense of humor back.

1906
02:58:00,383 --> 02:58:03,147
[Laughing]
Yeah.

1907
02:58:03,219 --> 02:58:06,484
I wondered what happened to it
during the ransom drop.

1908
02:58:09,892 --> 02:58:11,826
The ransom drop.

1909
02:58:11,894 --> 02:58:14,624
That was
a well-earned 12 million.

1910
02:58:15,832 --> 02:58:18,460
Twelve million.

1911
02:58:20,503 --> 02:58:23,165
Senator Rose says
he can pull strings.

1912
02:58:23,239 --> 02:58:27,175
He says he can fix it so you
keep the 12 million and walk.

1913
02:58:27,243 --> 02:58:32,054
All you have to do is return
the child. Where is Megan?

1914
02:58:33,189 --> 02:58:37,216
Where's Megan?
Where is Megan?

1915
02:58:37,293 --> 02:58:42,492
Where's Megan? Where is Megan?
Where is Megan?

1916
02:58:42,565 --> 02:58:45,557
She's trapped on my boat. Alex.
Isn't that right?

1917
02:58:45,634 --> 02:58:50,264
Or maybe she's stuck in a warehouse
somewhere or floating in a river.

1918
02:58:50,339 --> 02:58:53,274
Swinging from the end
of a rope. Buried alive.

1919
02:58:54,577 --> 02:58:56,670
[Snickers]

1920
02:58:58,480 --> 02:59:00,448
I envy her.

1921
02:59:03,953 --> 02:59:07,184
What would life had been like
with parents like that?

1922
02:59:07,256 --> 02:59:10,817
Come on, Gary, blaming your parents
for what you are?

1923
02:59:10,893 --> 02:59:13,521
I'm not blaming them, Alex.

1924
02:59:13,596 --> 02:59:17,293
They've been punished
already.

1925
02:59:22,671 --> 02:59:26,004
I burned down the house
while they slept.

1926
02:59:30,579 --> 02:59:33,548
I was 15 years old.

1927
02:59:33,616 --> 02:59:36,346
Was it what you expected?

1928
02:59:37,953 --> 02:59:41,081
Not really.
It was a new experience.

1929
02:59:41,156 --> 02:59:43,090
What. Killing?

1930
02:59:43,158 --> 02:59:47,026
No. Being
in the newspapers.

1931
02:59:50,299 --> 02:59:54,030
So, in your opinion, Doctor,

1932
02:59:54,103 --> 02:59:58,767
were my actions
triggered by nature...

1933
02:59:58,841 --> 03:00:00,900
or nurture?

1934
03:00:02,011 --> 03:00:04,479
If you want me
to be brutally honest...

1935
03:00:05,981 --> 03:00:10,577
I think you just have
a morbid desire to burn in hell.

1936
03:00:15,357 --> 03:00:17,552
[Quietly]
We're done for today.

1937
03:00:20,329 --> 03:00:22,854
I'm taking her with me.

1938
03:00:25,234 --> 03:00:28,260
[Groans]

1939
03:00:28,337 --> 03:00:32,000
- You're not taking her anywhere.
- I'll send her back to you.

1940
03:00:32,074 --> 03:00:34,542
You just tell me
which piece you want first.

1941
03:00:34,610 --> 03:00:37,704
Aah!

1942
03:00:37,780 --> 03:00:42,376
Ow! Oh, shit!
[Groaning]

1943
03:00:42,451 --> 03:00:44,851
Damn it.

1944
03:00:44,920 --> 03:00:47,718
Alex!

1945
03:00:50,626 --> 03:00:52,560
[Gasps]

1946
03:00:59,968 --> 03:01:02,562
Oh. My God.

1947
03:01:02,638 --> 03:01:04,902
What have you done?

1948
03:01:04,973 --> 03:01:09,808
[Sobbing]
What have you d-done?

1949
03:01:09,878 --> 03:01:12,574
[Sirens Wailing In Distance]

1950
03:01:12,715 --> 03:01:16,742
[Woman] Residents of this normally
quiet suburb are still in shock...

1951
03:01:16,819 --> 03:01:20,118
as news of the shooting of Gary
Soneji. America's most-wanted man.

1952
03:01:20,189 --> 03:01:22,123
Filtered through
their community.

1953
03:01:22,191 --> 03:01:24,523
Apparently, Soneji had attempted
to confront, or even harm...

1954
03:01:24,593 --> 03:01:27,118
members of the kidnapping
task force hunting him.

1955
03:01:27,196 --> 03:01:31,462
So. He came after Jezzie
as payback for Dimitri.

1956
03:01:32,935 --> 03:01:35,426
Ostensibly. Yeah.

1957
03:01:35,504 --> 03:01:37,438
That's how you want it
on record?

1958
03:01:37,506 --> 03:01:40,270
Yeah. For now.

1959
03:01:44,680 --> 03:01:46,807
Here they come.

1960
03:01:55,190 --> 03:01:59,092
Dr. Cross. Tell me you have at least
an idea where my little girl is.

1961
03:01:59,161 --> 03:02:02,255
I'm sorry. Sir. I can't.

1962
03:02:02,331 --> 03:02:04,799
You kill the one man
who has the answers.

1963
03:02:04,867 --> 03:02:08,598
And you're telling me
you haven't a clue. Not one clue?

1964
03:02:08,670 --> 03:02:11,798
The man walked in the fucking room.
And you shot him.

1965
03:02:11,874 --> 03:02:13,671
Senator...

1966
03:02:13,742 --> 03:02:16,370
standing in his shoes. I'd have
done the same thing. Sir.

1967
03:02:16,445 --> 03:02:20,575
That's your job. Not his. He's
supposed to find my little girl.

1968
03:02:20,649 --> 03:02:23,812
Not shoot the man
who knows where she is.

1969
03:02:23,886 --> 03:02:25,820
[MacArthur]
Senator.

1970
03:02:32,194 --> 03:02:34,128
It's not over.

1971
03:02:36,398 --> 03:02:39,890
The book is not closed.

1972
03:03:00,489 --> 03:03:02,423
Alex...

1973
03:03:05,060 --> 03:03:07,358
thank you
for saving my life.

1974
03:03:07,429 --> 03:03:09,363
Good-bye. Jezzie.

1975
03:03:16,905 --> 03:03:19,874
- Wanna hear something funny. Mac?
- Sure.

1976
03:03:19,942 --> 03:03:23,605
Cheer me up.

1977
03:03:23,679 --> 03:03:27,615
I congratulated Soneji
on scoring $ 12 million.

1978
03:03:27,683 --> 03:03:29,742
You mean ten million.

1979
03:03:31,653 --> 03:03:34,087
Exactly.

1980
03:03:34,156 --> 03:03:38,183
He had no idea
what I was talking about.

1981
03:03:52,708 --> 03:03:54,733
[Door Opens]

1982
03:04:02,184 --> 03:04:05,312
I know you.
You work at my school.

1983
03:04:06,688 --> 03:04:08,622
Eat your food. Megan.

1984
03:04:15,197 --> 03:04:18,098
[Door Closes, Locks]

1985
03:04:33,215 --> 03:04:35,410
[Watch Beeps]

1986
03:04:37,085 --> 03:04:39,019
[Watch Beeps]

1987
03:04:49,631 --> 03:04:51,565
[Watch Beeps]

1988
03:04:55,971 --> 03:04:58,496
Alex.
Where is this going?

1989
03:05:05,681 --> 03:05:09,208
We've been through these tapes
backwards and forwards.

1990
03:05:09,284 --> 03:05:11,479
I can't see how this is
helping us find Megan.

1991
03:05:14,289 --> 03:05:16,814
You know
what I see, Mac?

1992
03:05:16,892 --> 03:05:20,225
Someone was onto Soneji
long before we ever heard of him.

1993
03:05:20,295 --> 03:05:22,559
Look at this.
What do you see?

1994
03:05:22,631 --> 03:05:25,225
Agent Devine hauling ass
out to the front gate.

1995
03:05:25,300 --> 03:05:28,929
Mac. He could have shut this
whole place down from right there.

1996
03:05:29,004 --> 03:05:32,371
Now. You wanna tell me
why he didn't?

1997
03:05:35,444 --> 03:05:39,642
[Quietly] Good God.
Devine was in on it with him.

1998
03:05:39,715 --> 03:05:42,445
Then. When Soneji hit the embassy.
He pulled a double cross.

1999
03:05:42,517 --> 03:05:44,451
He ran his own ransom.

2000
03:05:44,519 --> 03:05:47,886
No. Soneji was a loner.

2001
03:05:47,956 --> 03:05:50,015
An accomplice would have
been beneath him.

2002
03:05:50,092 --> 03:05:52,754
I'll tell you
what happened.

2003
03:05:52,828 --> 03:05:55,558
Soneji was hoodwinked.

2004
03:05:57,299 --> 03:06:00,078
And so were we.

2005
03:06:00,212 --> 03:06:03,613
Details are still emerging.
But this much is clear:

2006
03:06:03,682 --> 03:06:07,083
The manunt that began over a
week ago in the natiors capitol...

2007
03:06:07,152 --> 03:06:09,450
- came to a violent end yesterday,
- [Clattering]

2008
03:06:09,521 --> 03:06:12,285
With the death of kidnapper,
Gary Soneji.

2009
03:06:45,290 --> 03:06:47,451
[Jezzie]
Don't move.

2010
03:06:47,526 --> 03:06:50,222
Turn around.
Hands on the wall. Feet apart.

2011
03:06:50,295 --> 03:06:52,229
Hi. Jez.
Where'd you come from?

2012
03:06:52,297 --> 03:06:55,164
You know something. Devine.
You're pretty stupid.

2013
03:06:55,233 --> 03:06:57,167
Your car in the driveway.

2014
03:06:57,235 --> 03:07:00,636
TV so loud. You wouldn't be able
to hear a SWAT team come in.

2015
03:07:00,705 --> 03:07:03,196
- What are you doing...
- Shut up!

2016
03:07:09,548 --> 03:07:11,675
[Both Laughing]

2017
03:07:19,457 --> 03:07:21,721
Where's Megan?

2018
03:07:21,793 --> 03:07:24,660
She's in the barn.
She was so doped up.

2019
03:07:24,729 --> 03:07:26,924
I don't think she knew
I took her off the boat.

2020
03:07:26,998 --> 03:07:30,058
She's still alive? You were
supposed to dump her in the river...

2021
03:07:30,135 --> 03:07:34,265
- after you got the diamonds.
- Yeah. Well.

2022
03:07:34,339 --> 03:07:38,332
Maybe killing a kid is something
I'm not prepared to do on my own.

2023
03:07:38,410 --> 03:07:41,208
Anyway. Today. Tomorrow. It's still
gonna look like Soneji killed her.

2024
03:07:41,279 --> 03:07:44,214
She can't die
after Soneji. You idiot.

2025
03:07:44,282 --> 03:07:47,740
It doesn't make any difference.
They're never gonna find the body.

2026
03:07:52,490 --> 03:07:56,517
Okay. I'll go do it now.
Will that make you happy?

2027
03:07:56,595 --> 03:08:00,725
Yeah. It would. Wait!

2028
03:08:04,369 --> 03:08:06,462
Can I see them?

2029
03:08:21,786 --> 03:08:24,016
Hey. Do you realize
we spent an entire year...

2030
03:08:24,089 --> 03:08:27,581
following Soneji's
every move?

2031
03:08:27,659 --> 03:08:30,059
I think
we deserve these.

2032
03:08:34,566 --> 03:08:38,263
That beats the hell out of
a Secret Service pension. Huh?

2033
03:08:39,504 --> 03:08:42,598
Profiling the profiler.

2034
03:08:42,674 --> 03:08:45,074
Kidnap from the kidnapper.
That's brilliant.

2035
03:08:45,143 --> 03:08:48,442
You are a genius. Jez.

2036
03:08:48,513 --> 03:08:51,710
Genius has nothing to do with it.
I'm just good at what I do.

2037
03:08:55,053 --> 03:08:58,181
Didrt hurt that everyone else
involved was a complete half-wit.

2038
03:08:58,256 --> 03:09:00,656
You think Alex Cross
is a half-wit?

2039
03:09:00,725 --> 03:09:04,422
You really believe that
he shot Soneji to save my life?

2040
03:09:04,496 --> 03:09:08,865
Cross pulled the trigger because
he knew Soneji didn't have Megan.

2041
03:09:10,735 --> 03:09:12,669
What are you saying?

2042
03:09:12,737 --> 03:09:16,138
I'm saying that sooner or later.
He's gonna figure it out.

2043
03:09:16,207 --> 03:09:18,675
He already knows Soneji
didn't run the ransom.

2044
03:09:20,445 --> 03:09:22,436
He's onto us already.
Isn't he?

2045
03:09:22,514 --> 03:09:25,608
No. He's not onto us.

2046
03:09:27,085 --> 03:09:30,316
But I think
he's onto you.

2047
03:10:03,054 --> 03:10:04,487
[Beeps]

2048
03:10:08,893 --> 03:10:11,088
[Computer Beeps]

2049
03:11:14,492 --> 03:11:17,950
It's Turkish. My daddy won it
in a game of poker.

2050
03:11:18,029 --> 03:11:21,021
That's about as much
as I know about my father.

2051
03:11:30,308 --> 03:11:32,003
[Beeps]

2052
03:12:23,294 --> 03:12:25,228
[Straining]

2053
03:13:04,002 --> 03:13:06,368
Megan?

2054
03:13:06,437 --> 03:13:08,496
Megan. It's me. Honey.

2055
03:13:08,573 --> 03:13:10,578
Jezzie?

2056
03:13:10,578 --> 03:13:11,510
Jezzie?

2057
03:13:11,579 --> 03:13:14,639
Jezzie. Jezzie.
I'm in here! Jezzie!

2058
03:13:14,715 --> 03:13:17,445
Open up. Honey. I'm gonna
take you home. It's all over.

2059
03:13:17,518 --> 03:13:20,248
Yeah. Sure.
Just hold on a second.

2060
03:13:20,321 --> 03:13:22,255
[Straining]

2061
03:13:26,994 --> 03:13:30,327
- Jezzie?
- Yeah. Honey.

2062
03:13:30,398 --> 03:13:33,094
What happened
to that other guy?

2063
03:13:35,636 --> 03:13:39,197
He's dead. Megan.
You're safe now.

2064
03:13:39,273 --> 03:13:42,106
Open up.

2065
03:13:42,176 --> 03:13:45,577
- Jezzie?
- Yeah, honey.

2066
03:13:45,646 --> 03:13:48,206
Why isn't there
anyone else with you?

2067
03:13:52,453 --> 03:13:56,617
Megan. It's me. Don't be
scared of me. Open the door.

2068
03:14:01,829 --> 03:14:04,957
Megan, I'm gonna ask you
one more time to open the door.

2069
03:14:05,032 --> 03:14:07,557
- Right now. Open the door!
- [Kicks Door]

2070
03:14:07,635 --> 03:14:10,160
Megan, open the door
for me.

2071
03:14:10,237 --> 03:14:12,705
Listen to me!
Open the door!

2072
03:14:12,773 --> 03:14:15,674
- [Kicking Door]
- Megan. Open the fucking door!

2073
03:14:15,743 --> 03:14:19,008
Open it, bitch!

2074
03:14:20,481 --> 03:14:22,711
- [Gunshot]
- [Screams]

2075
03:14:24,785 --> 03:14:27,913
Stop it! No!
[Screams]

2076
03:14:27,989 --> 03:14:29,923
Stop it!

2077
03:14:34,228 --> 03:14:36,162
[Breathing Heavily]

2078
03:14:45,773 --> 03:14:47,934
[Whimpering]

2079
03:15:39,794 --> 03:15:41,728
That was very clever.
Megan.

2080
03:15:49,837 --> 03:15:52,567
[Straining,
Whimpering]

2081
03:16:24,071 --> 03:16:27,131
- [Muffled Screams]
- Shh. Shh. Shh.

2082
03:17:10,584 --> 03:17:12,916
Jezzie?

2083
03:17:16,390 --> 03:17:18,858
It's over.

2084
03:17:18,926 --> 03:17:20,860
Drop the gun.

2085
03:17:24,765 --> 03:17:26,699
Alex...

2086
03:17:28,903 --> 03:17:30,837
how-how did you. Um...

2087
03:17:30,905 --> 03:17:33,237
Aces and eights. Jezzie.

2088
03:17:33,307 --> 03:17:36,868
Plus, your timing
was a little off.

2089
03:17:36,944 --> 03:17:38,878
I watched the tapes.

2090
03:17:38,946 --> 03:17:43,747
You and Devine could have
stopped Soneji at the school.

2091
03:17:43,817 --> 03:17:46,752
Just like you could have stopped
him at the Russian Embassy.

2092
03:17:46,820 --> 03:17:49,254
But you had
a different agenda.

2093
03:17:49,323 --> 03:17:52,451
You know something. Alex?

2094
03:17:52,526 --> 03:17:54,619
When you said.
"You do what you are."

2095
03:17:54,695 --> 03:17:57,220
You were right.

2096
03:17:57,298 --> 03:18:00,426
I'm living proof.

2097
03:18:01,702 --> 03:18:04,193
Put the gun down. Jezzie.

2098
03:18:09,977 --> 03:18:13,276
Would you kill
another partner?

2099
03:18:13,347 --> 03:18:16,077
You're not my partner.

2100
03:18:23,390 --> 03:18:25,722
[Whimpering]

2101
03:19:31,191 --> 03:19:33,352
Are you all right?

2102
03:19:35,929 --> 03:19:38,124
You're a very brave girl.
Megan.

2103
03:19:38,198 --> 03:19:41,292
Who are you?

2104
03:19:41,368 --> 03:19:44,303
I'm a policeman.

2105
03:19:47,474 --> 03:19:50,409
My name is Alex Cross.

2106
03:19:50,477 --> 03:19:53,037
I'm a friend
of your parents.

2107
03:19:56,650 --> 03:19:58,880
Can you take me to them?

2108
03:20:00,353 --> 03:20:03,083
Nothing would give me
greater pleasure.

2109
03:20:06,793 --> 03:20:10,593
Could you...
Ah. Thanks.
